WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.219 --> 00:00:18.552
[water flowing]

2
00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:27.685
[suspenseful music]

3
00:00:27.687 --> 00:00:30.452
-[Dida]
<i>The world we knew is gone.</i>

4
00:00:31.887 --> 00:00:33.585
<i>Three hundred years ago.</i>

5
00:00:33.753 --> 00:00:36.452
<i>the great flood swallowed</i>
<i>the land.</i>

6
00:00:36.619 --> 00:00:39.219
<i>leaving nothing</i>
<i>but scattered islands</i>

7
00:00:39.386 --> 00:00:41.519
<i>and an ocean without end.</i>

8
00:00:43.687 --> 00:00:47.353
[men chanting]

9
00:00:47.519 --> 00:00:51.853
<i>Above us the sky churns</i>
<i>with a storm that never fades.</i>

10
00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:56.753
[men chanting continues]

11
00:00:58.753 --> 00:01:02.286
<i>Below. the Old World.</i>
<i>its cities.</i>

12
00:01:02.452 --> 00:01:05.319
<i>its knowledge. lost to time.</i>

13
00:01:08.219 --> 00:01:10.787
[ominous music]

14
00:01:10.953 --> 00:01:13.519
<i>But not all was lost.</i>

15
00:01:13.687 --> 00:01:17.550
<i>From the ruins.</i>
<i>Argos was built.</i>

16
00:01:17.552 --> 00:01:20.319
<i>a city of towering walls.</i>

17
00:01:20.485 --> 00:01:23.685
<i>shimmering lights</i>
<i>and secrets buried deeper</i>

18
00:01:23.687 --> 00:01:26.753
<i>than the sea itself.</i>

19
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:30.353
<i>Argos is ruled</i>
<i>by the Founders. Titans.</i>

20
00:01:30.519 --> 00:01:33.787
<i>believed to be as old</i>
<i>as the world they built.</i>

21
00:01:33.953 --> 00:01:37.450
<i>They rule from their citadel.</i>
<i>preaching safety.</i>

22
00:01:37.452 --> 00:01:41.286
<i>but their safety</i>
<i>comes with a price.</i>

23
00:01:42.219 --> 00:01:45.186
<i>To live in Argos.</i>
<i>you must earn it.</i>

24
00:01:46.853 --> 00:01:51.450
<i>Storm riding. a death race</i>
<i>of speed and survival.</i>

25
00:01:51.452 --> 00:01:54.685
<i>where only the most relentless</i>
<i>can claim victory.</i>

26
00:01:54.687 --> 00:01:55.718
[eerie music]

27
00:01:55.720 --> 00:01:59.653
<i>You win and your people</i>
<i>are granted entry.</i>

28
00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:03.419
<i>You lose and your island</i>
<i>is stripped bare.</i>

29
00:02:03.586 --> 00:02:06.785
<i>its people cast</i>
<i>into the open sea.</i>

30
00:02:06.787 --> 00:02:08.450
[eerie music continues]

31
00:02:08.452 --> 00:02:10.753
<i>That is the law of the Founders.</i>

32
00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:13.653
<i>That is the price of survival.</i>

33
00:02:13.820 --> 00:02:16.286
[tense music]

34
00:02:16.452 --> 00:02:18.419
<i>For generations.</i>
<i>the Islanders were told</i>

35
00:02:18.586 --> 00:02:21.887
<i>that racing for Argos</i>
<i>is the only way.</i>

36
00:02:22.253 --> 00:02:24.920
<i>But some of them believe</i>
<i>in more.</i>

37
00:02:25.286 --> 00:02:29.651
<i>a legend that speaks of the one</i>
<i>who will set them free.</i>

38
00:02:29.653 --> 00:02:31.885
<i>the promised one.</i>

39
00:02:31.887 --> 00:02:35.450
<i>But this isn't the story</i>
<i>of the promised one.</i>

40
00:02:35.452 --> 00:02:40.316
<i>This is a story of a promise.</i>
<i>a promise of love.</i>

41
00:02:40.318 --> 00:02:44.520
<i>A promise to fight.</i>
<i>A promise to rise.</i>

42
00:02:44.687 --> 00:02:46.753
-[Race Announcer]
<i>Three. two. one.</i>

43
00:02:46.920 --> 00:02:48.419
[alarm honking]

44
00:02:48.586 --> 00:02:53.551
[machine whirring]

45
00:02:53.553 --> 00:02:55.352
[thunder rolls softly]

46
00:02:58.887 --> 00:03:02.920
[tense music]

47
00:03:11.318 --> 00:03:12.352
[insects chirping]

48
00:03:13.419 --> 00:03:15.887
[church bell ringing]

49
00:03:18.318 --> 00:03:19.553
-[Neb]
<i>Hammerhead.</i>

50
00:03:20.419 --> 00:03:22.285
-[Neb] <i>The Founders</i>
<i>declared him a criminal.</i>

51
00:03:22.452 --> 00:03:23.887
<i>a wanted outlaw.</i>

52
00:03:24.252 --> 00:03:26.853
<i>but to some of us.</i>
<i>he was a path to follow.</i>

53
00:03:28.186 --> 00:03:30.687
-[Radio Announcer] <i>Where will</i>
<i>you be when the storm hits?</i>

54
00:03:30.853 --> 00:03:33.653
<i>Are you afraid</i>
<i>it will destroy your island?</i>

55
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:35.885
<i>Do not despair. Islanders.</i>

56
00:03:35.887 --> 00:03:38.520
<i>You can secure</i>
<i>your island's safety</i>

57
00:03:38.687 --> 00:03:41.417
<i>behind the walls of Argos.</i>

58
00:03:41.419 --> 00:03:43.553
<i>Simply put up your island</i>
<i>as collateral.</i>

59
00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:45.352
<i>and one</i>
<i>of our generous Founders</i>

60
00:03:45.520 --> 00:03:48.687
<i>may sponsor your selected riders</i>
<i>to join the league.</i>

61
00:03:48.853 --> 00:03:51.551
<i>to win a race and win a place</i>

62
00:03:51.553 --> 00:03:55.853
<i>for those living on your island</i>
<i>behind the walls of Argos.</i>

63
00:03:56.218 --> 00:03:59.586
<i>Your safety is one race away.</i>

64
00:04:02.653 --> 00:04:04.620
-Neb.
Give me a nine.

65
00:04:07.687 --> 00:04:08.753
[object thuds]

66
00:04:09.553 --> 00:04:11.653
-Neb. you gotta see this.

67
00:04:11.820 --> 00:04:12.953
[grunts]

68
00:04:13.653 --> 00:04:14.551
-[man in the background]
<i>Torpedo's on.</i>

69
00:04:14.553 --> 00:04:15.653
<i>Come on. come on.</i>

70
00:04:17.453 --> 00:04:18.451
-Wicked. right?

71
00:04:18.453 --> 00:04:19.553
-[man in the background]
All systems are go.

72
00:04:21.753 --> 00:04:23.853
-They call him Hammerhead.

73
00:04:24.218 --> 00:04:25.753
Legend has it
he was struck by lightning

74
00:04:26.553 --> 00:04:28.453
and sacrificed himself
to the storm.

75
00:04:28.620 --> 00:04:29.753
[somber music]

76
00:04:29.920 --> 00:04:31.653
They say
he saved his whole island

77
00:04:32.753 --> 00:04:34.653
and never lost a single ride.

78
00:04:36.687 --> 00:04:39.316
Some believe he actually broke
through the storm

79
00:04:39.318 --> 00:04:41.316
and came out the other side.

80
00:04:41.318 --> 00:04:43.318
Others believed
that he still crashes the race

81
00:04:43.486 --> 00:04:44.451
from time to time

82
00:04:44.453 --> 00:04:47.687
so he can win a place
for all Islanders.

83
00:04:48.887 --> 00:04:50.887
That could be us one day.

84
00:04:51.252 --> 00:04:53.285
-[indistinct]

85
00:04:53.453 --> 00:04:54.586
-Who needs legends?

86
00:04:55.687 --> 00:04:57.520
You don't have Hammerhead.
You have me.

87
00:04:57.687 --> 00:04:59.420
[soft tense music]

88
00:04:59.586 --> 00:05:01.751
You kids watch.

89
00:05:01.753 --> 00:05:02.885
If anyone's gonna
catch lightning.

90
00:05:02.887 --> 00:05:04.285
it's gonna be me.

91
00:05:06.753 --> 00:05:08.318
[soft kiss]
[engine starts]

92
00:05:08.486 --> 00:05:09.352
Let's go. kids!

93
00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:11.285
-[indistinct shouting]

94
00:05:11.453 --> 00:05:12.751
-Come on. kids.
Gotta go.

95
00:05:12.753 --> 00:05:16.352
[machine whirring]

96
00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:17.520
[kisses photo]

97
00:05:17.687 --> 00:05:19.420
[palm smack]

98
00:05:19.586 --> 00:05:23.653
[chain clinking]

99
00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:25.418
[metal clangs]

100
00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:26.453
-Come on.

101
00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:29.420
[footsteps running]

102
00:05:29.586 --> 00:05:30.316
[quick palm smack]

103
00:05:30.318 --> 00:05:31.787
-Once you get to Neptune's Rock.

104
00:05:33.285 --> 00:05:36.285
you'll have 10 seconds
to break away.

105
00:05:36.453 --> 00:05:37.553
-Okay.

106
00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:38.653
I will go through it.

107
00:05:39.753 --> 00:05:42.283
The Storm Horizon will fall.

108
00:05:42.285 --> 00:05:44.518
-Just be aware
of the bombheads. all right?

109
00:05:44.520 --> 00:05:45.818
-Okay.
Let's go.

110
00:05:45.820 --> 00:05:48.920
-[Neb] <i>The Legend Of Hammerhead</i>
<i>was more than just a story.</i>

111
00:05:49.285 --> 00:05:50.820
<i>It meant hope.</i>

112
00:05:51.586 --> 00:05:53.920
<i>A reason to believe there was</i>
<i>something beyond the storm.</i>

113
00:05:54.285 --> 00:05:56.185
-Stay with the truth. kids.

114
00:05:58.218 --> 00:06:01.787
-[Neb] <i>Among those who believed</i>
<i>was Lazar. Ana's father.</i>

115
00:06:01.953 --> 00:06:04.183
<i>While others</i>
<i>raced for victory.</i>

116
00:06:04.185 --> 00:06:05.687
<i>he didn't care about winning.</i>

117
00:06:05.853 --> 00:06:07.319
<i>His mission</i>
<i>was to breach the storm</i>

118
00:06:07.486 --> 00:06:08.651
<i>and see what lies beyond.</i>

119
00:06:08.653 --> 00:06:09.887
[tense music]

120
00:06:10.252 --> 00:06:10.885
-[Race Announcer]
<i>Broadcasting live</i>

121
00:06:10.887 --> 00:06:12.453
<i>from the walls of Argos.</i>

122
00:06:12.620 --> 00:06:14.553
<i>this is the final race</i>
<i>of the season</i>

123
00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:17.853
<i>as our contesting Storm Riders</i>
<i>eagerly await the countdown.</i>

124
00:06:18.218 --> 00:06:19.653
<i>This is a drag race</i>
<i>from starting point</i>

125
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.851
<i>to Neptune's Rock</i>
<i>and back again.</i>

126
00:06:21.853 --> 00:06:23.553
<i>Winners win a place on Argos.</i>

127
00:06:23.720 --> 00:06:26.285
<i>Losers are cast out</i>
<i>to the open sea.</i>

128
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:28.283
<i>Here are the islands competing:</i>

129
00:06:28.285 --> 00:06:32.586
<i>Avalon. Cios. Malia</i>
<i>and this year's clear underdog.</i>

130
00:06:32.753 --> 00:06:36.553
<i>Fig Island has come forth</i>
<i>with their selected champion.</i>

131
00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:37.618
<i>Who would have thought?</i>

132
00:06:37.620 --> 00:06:39.420
<i>As always.</i>
<i>the race will be policed</i>

133
00:06:39.586 --> 00:06:40.751
<i>by the Argos riders.</i>

134
00:06:40.753 --> 00:06:43.518
<i>or as some. including myself.</i>
<i>like to call them.</i>

135
00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:44.853
<i>the bombheads.</i>

136
00:06:45.218 --> 00:06:47.286
[tense music]

137
00:06:47.453 --> 00:06:48.687
[machine whirring]

138
00:06:48.853 --> 00:06:50.553
<i>And they're off to the races.</i>

139
00:06:51.753 --> 00:06:53.553
[engine rumbling]

140
00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:55.218
<i>A great start for Avalon riders.</i>

141
00:06:55.386 --> 00:06:56.851
<i>who jump out in front</i>
<i>with Argos riders</i>

142
00:06:56.853 --> 00:06:58.518
<i>right behind them.</i>

143
00:06:58.520 --> 00:07:00.851
<i>and Fig Island. Cios and Malia</i>
<i>fighting for position.</i>

144
00:07:00.853 --> 00:07:03.553
[suspenseful music]

145
00:07:03.720 --> 00:07:05.353
-They should be coming
around here soon.

146
00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:09.687
[engine rumbling]

147
00:07:13.753 --> 00:07:15.286
Wicked. right?

148
00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:18.653
-[Race Announcer]
<i>Fig island's rider gets closer</i>

149
00:07:18.820 --> 00:07:19.918
<i>and closer to Avalon riders.</i>

150
00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:23.218
<i>who slows down.</i>
<i>bumps into him and cuts him off.</i>

151
00:07:28.286 --> 00:07:31.218
[engine rumbling]

152
00:07:31.386 --> 00:07:34.183
[lightning static]

153
00:07:34.185 --> 00:07:36.353
<i>And the rider</i>
<i>from Cios catches lightning.</i>

154
00:07:36.520 --> 00:07:38.286
<i>giving him a boost.</i>

155
00:07:38.453 --> 00:07:40.518
<i>He takes over first position.</i>

156
00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:42.620
[intense music]

157
00:07:44.453 --> 00:07:47.183
[ominous music]

158
00:07:47.185 --> 00:07:48.751
[water splashes]

159
00:07:48.753 --> 00:07:52.353
<i>Another race full</i>
<i>of mayhem and destruction.</i>

160
00:07:52.520 --> 00:07:53.586
-Steer back.

161
00:07:53.753 --> 00:07:54.853
We gotta get back
to the tunnel.

162
00:07:55.219 --> 00:07:57.787
[intense music]

163
00:08:01.753 --> 00:08:03.753
[water splashing]

164
00:08:03.920 --> 00:08:07.586
[engine rumbling]

165
00:08:07.753 --> 00:08:08.885
[boat explodes]

166
00:08:08.887 --> 00:08:10.520
-[Race Announcer]
<i>Oh. and the second Cios rider</i>

167
00:08:10.687 --> 00:08:11.851
<i>crashes on the rocks.</i>

168
00:08:11.853 --> 00:08:15.353
<i>The island of Cios</i>
<i>is now officially declared lost.</i>

169
00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:17.386
<i>But the race</i>
<i>for the winner continues.</i>

170
00:08:17.553 --> 00:08:20.952
<i>Malia. Avalon. Argos riders</i>
<i>circling Neptune's Rock.</i>

171
00:08:21.319 --> 00:08:23.586
<i>The front runner from Avalon</i>
<i>comes way out ahead.</i>

172
00:08:23.753 --> 00:08:24.885
<i>If he crosses the finish line.</i>

173
00:08:24.887 --> 00:08:27.453
<i>the island of Avalon</i>
<i>will be heading to Argos.</i>

174
00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:29.186
[intense music]

175
00:08:29.353 --> 00:08:31.284
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>what I'm seeing right now.</i>

176
00:08:31.286 --> 00:08:32.217
[lightning crackles]

177
00:08:32.219 --> 00:08:34.853
<i>The Fig Island rider</i>
<i>is breaking off.</i>

178
00:08:35.219 --> 00:08:37.219
<i>It seems we have a rebel rider</i>
<i>in our midst.</i>

179
00:08:37.386 --> 00:08:38.384
<i>This is the fifth incident</i>

180
00:08:38.386 --> 00:08:41.286
<i>this season</i>
<i>of such suicidal behavior.</i>

181
00:08:41.453 --> 00:08:42.851
<i>What are these people thinking?</i>

182
00:08:42.853 --> 00:08:44.319
[engine humming]

183
00:08:44.486 --> 00:08:46.586
[water splashing]

184
00:08:46.753 --> 00:08:48.420
[thunder rumbling]

185
00:08:48.586 --> 00:08:49.518
<i>Lazar from Fig Island</i>

186
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:50.952
<i>seems to be heading</i>
<i>for the storm.</i>

187
00:08:51.319 --> 00:08:53.353
[intense music]

188
00:08:53.520 --> 00:08:54.887
[accelerator clicks]

189
00:08:55.253 --> 00:08:55.785
[lightning static]

190
00:08:55.787 --> 00:08:56.853
[machine whirring]

191
00:08:59.586 --> 00:09:01.284
[intense music continues]

192
00:09:01.286 --> 00:09:04.420
[lightning static]

193
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:06.687
[thunder rumbling]

194
00:09:06.853 --> 00:09:10.787
[lightning static]

195
00:09:10.952 --> 00:09:12.451
[boat explodes]

196
00:09:12.453 --> 00:09:15.919
<i>When will these pagans learn.</i>
<i>no one survives the storm.</i>

197
00:09:16.286 --> 00:09:17.217
[distant cheering and
applauding]

198
00:09:17.219 --> 00:09:18.753
<i>Four riders dead</i>
<i>on the water today.</i>

199
00:09:18.919 --> 00:09:20.851
<i>The island of Cios</i>
<i>has come in last place.</i>

200
00:09:20.853 --> 00:09:23.553
<i>Their people will be evacuated</i>
<i>and the stones from their island</i>

201
00:09:23.720 --> 00:09:25.919
<i>will become forever part</i>
<i>of our wall.</i>

202
00:09:26.286 --> 00:09:28.286
<i>May the mercy of the deep</i>
<i>be upon them.</i>

203
00:09:28.453 --> 00:09:30.186
<i>As far as Fig Island.</i>

204
00:09:30.353 --> 00:09:32.787
<i>they will be banned from racing</i>
<i>for the next ten years</i>

205
00:09:32.952 --> 00:09:34.753
<i>because of their treachery.</i>

206
00:09:34.919 --> 00:09:38.386
-[Neb] <i>After her father died.</i>
<i>Ana locked her pain inside.</i>

207
00:09:38.553 --> 00:09:41.353
<i>But she swore that one day.</i>
<i>she would avenge him.</i>

208
00:09:41.520 --> 00:09:42.620
[school bell rings]

209
00:09:42.787 --> 00:09:45.219
[footsteps running]

210
00:09:45.386 --> 00:09:48.853
[somber music]

211
00:09:51.553 --> 00:09:55.753
-Here.
An island with Titans.

212
00:09:55.919 --> 00:09:57.886
[chuckles]

213
00:09:58.253 --> 00:10:01.620
-There are no islands
past the Storm Horizon. Neb.

214
00:10:01.787 --> 00:10:02.952
-Blastheads.

215
00:10:03.319 --> 00:10:04.386
-Shut up. you little punk!

216
00:10:04.553 --> 00:10:06.952
-Ana! please.

217
00:10:07.319 --> 00:10:11.353
Class. what do we know
about the Storm Horizon?

218
00:10:12.753 --> 00:10:13.884
[stick thumps]

219
00:10:13.886 --> 00:10:16.952
-We're lucky to be protected
by the Storm Horizon.

220
00:10:17.319 --> 00:10:18.886
-Very good. Tom.

221
00:10:19.253 --> 00:10:21.586
-The storm is a lie
created by the Founders.

222
00:10:21.753 --> 00:10:22.420
(laughs)

223
00:10:22.586 --> 00:10:23.720
-Quiet!

224
00:10:23.886 --> 00:10:25.386
[groans]

225
00:10:27.453 --> 00:10:29.186
-He has quite
the imagination.

226
00:10:30.319 --> 00:10:34.486
But we simply cannot accept him
disrespecting our Founders.

227
00:10:34.653 --> 00:10:36.386
our benefactors.

228
00:10:36.553 --> 00:10:38.486
He's talking
about mythical islands.

229
00:10:38.653 --> 00:10:40.687
rebel riders...

230
00:10:40.852 --> 00:10:43.286
-[Neb] <i>Legend has it</i>
<i>he was struck by lightning</i>

231
00:10:43.453 --> 00:10:45.219
<i>and sacrificed himself</i>
<i>to the storm.</i>

232
00:10:45.386 --> 00:10:48.520
[men chanting]

233
00:10:48.687 --> 00:10:49.886
[thunder rumbling]

234
00:10:50.253 --> 00:10:53.687
[lightning static]

235
00:10:53.852 --> 00:10:58.453
[ominous music]

236
00:10:58.620 --> 00:11:00.319
-Neb. you have to get down!

237
00:11:03.219 --> 00:11:04.886
Come down!

238
00:11:05.253 --> 00:11:06.420
Neb. come on!

239
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:09.687
[lightning static]

240
00:11:09.852 --> 00:11:12.486
Neb. you have to get down!

241
00:11:12.653 --> 00:11:13.620
Neb!

242
00:11:13.786 --> 00:11:15.553
Argh!

243
00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:17.753
[lightning static explodes]

244
00:11:21.420 --> 00:11:23.586
[heart pounding]

245
00:11:23.753 --> 00:11:27.786
[men chanting]

246
00:11:30.786 --> 00:11:34.687
[wind blowing]

247
00:11:34.852 --> 00:11:35.952
-[Neb] <i>Legend says</i>
that the Hammerhead

248
00:11:36.319 --> 00:11:37.852
<i>was struck by lightning.</i>

249
00:11:38.219 --> 00:11:41.253
<i>So I figured it was my turn</i>
<i>to stand for Ana.</i>

250
00:11:41.420 --> 00:11:43.687
<i>to face the storm.</i>
<i>to be tested.</i>

251
00:11:43.852 --> 00:11:45.420
<i>Because only those</i>
<i>who survived the storm</i>

252
00:11:45.586 --> 00:11:47.786
<i>gained the power</i>
<i>to break through it.</i>

253
00:11:47.952 --> 00:11:50.620
[ominous music fades]

254
00:11:50.786 --> 00:11:52.453
-[Radio Announcer] <i>The rider</i>
<i>from Fig Island was killed</i>

255
00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:54.553
<i>while attempting</i>
<i>to breach the storm.</i>

256
00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:57.219
<i>As a consequence of this</i>
<i>criminal behavior.</i>

257
00:11:57.386 --> 00:11:59.353
<i>Fig Island will face</i>
<i>a ten year suspension</i>

258
00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:01.852
<i>from any future racing.</i>

259
00:12:02.219 --> 00:12:04.752
<i>But the real tragedy befalls</i>
<i>the people of Cios.</i>

260
00:12:04.919 --> 00:12:07.653
<i>whose two selected riders</i>
<i>crashed mid-race.</i>

261
00:12:07.819 --> 00:12:09.620
<i>never making it</i>
<i>to the finish line.</i>

262
00:12:09.786 --> 00:12:12.786
<i>resulting in their island</i>
<i>facing eviction.</i>

263
00:12:12.953 --> 00:12:14.886
<i>May the mercy of the deep</i>
<i>be upon them.</i>

264
00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:17.353
[church bell ringing]

265
00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.353
<i>-Pagans of Cios.</i>

266
00:12:19.520 --> 00:12:22.253
<i>your attempt</i>
<i>to join Argos has failed.</i>

267
00:12:22.420 --> 00:12:24.786
<i>The rider you chose</i>
<i>has failed you.</i>

268
00:12:24.953 --> 00:12:28.219
<i>Your worship</i>
<i>of Gaya has failed you.</i>

269
00:12:28.386 --> 00:12:31.786
[distant arguments]

270
00:12:31.953 --> 00:12:35.953
[suspenseful music]

271
00:12:36.319 --> 00:12:39.453
Cios is now property
of Lord Tarus.

272
00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:42.186
Open sea is your new home.

273
00:12:42.353 --> 00:12:44.586
May the mercy of the traitor--

274
00:12:44.752 --> 00:12:45.586
[man grunts]

275
00:12:45.752 --> 00:12:46.653
-That's enough.

276
00:12:48.319 --> 00:12:51.486
[distant shouting]

277
00:12:57.186 --> 00:12:58.819
[man grunts]
[man groans]

278
00:12:59.186 --> 00:13:00.420
-[woman] Stop resisting!

279
00:13:00.586 --> 00:13:02.953
[intense music]

280
00:13:03.319 --> 00:13:05.553
-[Neb] <i>The Founders</i>
<i>aren't just taking islands.</i>

281
00:13:05.719 --> 00:13:07.319
<i>they're tearing them apart</i>

282
00:13:07.486 --> 00:13:09.819
<i>while searching</i>
<i>for something ancient.</i>

283
00:13:10.186 --> 00:13:12.286
<i>The nucleus of life itself.</i>

284
00:13:12.453 --> 00:13:14.819
<i>nature's final bid for rebirth.</i>

285
00:13:15.186 --> 00:13:17.586
<i>A substance very few know about.</i>

286
00:13:17.752 --> 00:13:21.319
<i>whispered to defy death itself:</i>
<i>the element.</i>

287
00:13:22.686 --> 00:13:24.852
[intense music fades]

288
00:13:26.186 --> 00:13:28.652
<i>I felt death crawling</i>
<i>through my veins.</i>

289
00:13:28.819 --> 00:13:31.719
<i>my eyes ablaze with fire.</i>

290
00:13:31.887 --> 00:13:33.386
<i>But then my grandfather</i>
<i>did something</i>

291
00:13:33.553 --> 00:13:35.353
<i>he swore</i>
<i>he would never do again.</i>

292
00:13:36.286 --> 00:13:39.852
[birds chirping]

293
00:13:48.586 --> 00:13:52.853
[suspenseful music]

294
00:13:53.219 --> 00:13:53.887
[ax clinks]

295
00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:11.219
[ax thuds]

296
00:14:11.386 --> 00:14:15.386
[liquid flowing]

297
00:14:17.286 --> 00:14:22.219
[suspenseful music continues]

298
00:14:32.386 --> 00:14:34.319
<i>Then the visions came.</i>

299
00:14:34.486 --> 00:14:37.453
<i>A flash of lightning.</i>
<i>a tear in time.</i>

300
00:14:37.619 --> 00:14:39.920
<i>And there he was.</i>
<i>the Hammerhead.</i>

301
00:14:40.286 --> 00:14:44.719
[tense music]

302
00:14:45.585 --> 00:14:47.520
[distant conversation]

303
00:14:47.686 --> 00:14:49.652
[horn blowing]

304
00:14:49.820 --> 00:14:51.752
[suspenseful music]

305
00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:54.853
[footsteps approaching]

306
00:14:59.186 --> 00:15:02.319
-Our excavations
revealed no new source.

307
00:15:02.486 --> 00:15:03.585
Nothing.

308
00:15:03.752 --> 00:15:05.686
-How many islands remain?

309
00:15:05.853 --> 00:15:06.752
-For plundering?

310
00:15:06.920 --> 00:15:07.887
-How many?

311
00:15:08.253 --> 00:15:09.719
-Just over 2.000.

312
00:15:12.486 --> 00:15:14.353
-How much element
do we have left. Tarus?

313
00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:17.853
-A decade in reserve.
maybe less.

314
00:15:19.853 --> 00:15:21.619
-Then we take the islands
by force.

315
00:15:21.787 --> 00:15:25.486
-You cross that line
and you remind the islanders

316
00:15:25.652 --> 00:15:27.920
that even
with our combined forces.

317
00:15:28.286 --> 00:15:30.719
they outnumber us.
a thousand to one.

318
00:15:32.552 --> 00:15:35.353
You'll die
before that well runs dry.

319
00:15:36.719 --> 00:15:41.585
It's time for us
to accept our fate.

320
00:15:41.753 --> 00:15:44.253
-I make my fate. Baroness.

321
00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:46.386
-Amor fati.

322
00:15:46.552 --> 00:15:49.286
-I've heard those words before.

323
00:15:49.453 --> 00:15:52.420
-It's just a saying
from the old world. Tarus.

324
00:15:52.585 --> 00:15:53.552
[scoffs]

325
00:15:54.753 --> 00:15:57.420
No. that was his <i>saying.</i>

326
00:15:57.585 --> 00:16:02.720
The traitor. the thief.
Sykeus.

327
00:16:05.787 --> 00:16:07.552
We cannot take the islands
by force.

328
00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:11.353
So instead. the heathens
will give them to us.

329
00:16:12.652 --> 00:16:14.420
We'll increase the races.

330
00:16:14.585 --> 00:16:16.253
The more pagans
bleed out in the water.

331
00:16:16.420 --> 00:16:19.953
the closer we'll be to finding
a new source of the element.

332
00:16:20.319 --> 00:16:22.787
Besides. those suicidal riders

333
00:16:22.953 --> 00:16:26.219
are getting too frequent
to ignore.

334
00:16:26.386 --> 00:16:27.619
Oh. and Baroness...

335
00:16:34.687 --> 00:16:37.652
Do not say his words
to me again.

336
00:16:39.853 --> 00:16:43.652
[ominous music]

337
00:16:43.820 --> 00:16:46.519
[footsteps departing]

338
00:16:46.687 --> 00:16:48.386
[birds chirping]

339
00:16:48.552 --> 00:16:51.253
[wind blowing]

340
00:16:54.319 --> 00:16:55.317
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>The island of Cios</i>

341
00:16:55.319 --> 00:16:57.820
<i>has been evacuated</i>
<i>by decree of Argos.</i>

342
00:16:58.186 --> 00:16:59.217
<i>its inhabitants...</i>

343
00:16:59.219 --> 00:17:02.687
-Maybe one day.
you'll be able to make fig jam

344
00:17:02.853 --> 00:17:04.753
as good as your old grandfather.

345
00:17:06.552 --> 00:17:08.585
Just maybe.
[chuckles]

346
00:17:08.753 --> 00:17:10.319
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>As far as the recent conduct</i>

347
00:17:10.485 --> 00:17:11.887
<i>by the Fig Island's rider.</i>

348
00:17:12.253 --> 00:17:14.485
<i>our lord Founders</i>
<i>have shown leniency.</i>

349
00:17:14.653 --> 00:17:16.485
-No. it's [indistinct].

350
00:17:16.653 --> 00:17:17.787
-[radio announcer continues]
<i>a temporary ban for a chance</i>

351
00:17:17.953 --> 00:17:20.552
<i>of winning</i>
<i>a place on Argos.</i>

352
00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:21.851
-Look at this. huh?
[chuckles]

353
00:17:21.853 --> 00:17:23.583
-[Radio Announcer]
... <i>that any future attempts</i>

354
00:17:23.585 --> 00:17:28.353
<i>to breach the storm will result</i>
<i>in permanent disqualification.</i>

355
00:17:28.519 --> 00:17:31.219
<i>as such actions pose</i>
<i>a great risk to our...</i>

356
00:17:31.386 --> 00:17:35.753
[somber music]

357
00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:37.820
-[Neb]
<i>Visions come suddenly.</i>

358
00:17:38.186 --> 00:17:39.485
<i>Unexpectedly.</i>

359
00:17:39.653 --> 00:17:41.687
[suspenseful music]

360
00:17:41.853 --> 00:17:44.186
<i>Like the flash of lightning</i>
<i>that made me see.</i>

361
00:17:46.720 --> 00:17:49.519
<i>There he was again.</i>
<i>haunting me.</i>

362
00:17:49.687 --> 00:17:50.951
<i>staring back at me.</i>

363
00:17:50.953 --> 00:17:52.953
-[Radio Announcer] <i>By decree</i>
<i>of Argos. its inhabitants</i>

364
00:17:53.319 --> 00:17:55.820
<i>now join the growing number</i>
<i>of displaced people</i>

365
00:17:56.186 --> 00:17:58.519
<i>taking refuge at deep sea.</i>

366
00:17:58.687 --> 00:18:01.820
<i>Islanders are urged to halt</i>
<i>this reckless behavior</i>

367
00:18:02.186 --> 00:18:03.687
<i>for the safety of all.</i>

368
00:18:03.853 --> 00:18:07.452
[suspenseful music continues]

369
00:18:07.620 --> 00:18:10.485
[water splashing]

370
00:18:11.620 --> 00:18:14.586
<i>-Is this the one</i>
<i>the legends speak of?</i>

371
00:18:14.753 --> 00:18:16.920
<i>-Thought he was still seeing</i>
<i>storm riding.</i>

372
00:18:21.552 --> 00:18:24.653
[birds chirping]

373
00:18:28.620 --> 00:18:30.687
-Still no sign of Sykeus.
my lord.

374
00:18:32.319 --> 00:18:36.286
But we have found
his wreckage.

375
00:18:37.286 --> 00:18:38.552
-Where?

376
00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:40.720
-The Bay of Gaya. my lord.

377
00:18:43.720 --> 00:18:45.953
As the Islanders call it.

378
00:18:46.319 --> 00:18:47.787
-So Sykeus is near.

379
00:18:50.186 --> 00:18:52.820
Send every spy
to each and every island

380
00:18:53.186 --> 00:18:54.586
around the wreckage.

381
00:18:54.753 --> 00:18:56.318
-That's hundreds of islands.

382
00:18:57.485 --> 00:19:00.753
-So take the Baroness
and her troops and find him!

383
00:19:03.820 --> 00:19:05.253
[suspenseful music fades]

384
00:19:05.419 --> 00:19:09.820
[gentle music]

385
00:19:10.186 --> 00:19:13.753
[seagulls squawking]

386
00:19:17.920 --> 00:19:22.253
[insects chirping]

387
00:19:28.419 --> 00:19:31.687
-I have seen her flag
on the coast.

388
00:19:31.853 --> 00:19:33.820
[thunder rumbles softly]

389
00:19:34.154 --> 00:19:35.653
She is coming for him.

390
00:19:35.820 --> 00:19:38.820
[suspenseful music]

391
00:19:39.186 --> 00:19:40.920
-[Neb] <i>Argos wants</i>
Hammerhead found.

392
00:19:41.285 --> 00:19:43.953
<i>so word of his hideout</i>
<i>spread fast.</i>

393
00:19:44.318 --> 00:19:45.283
<i>Ana was taking me to see</i>

394
00:19:45.285 --> 00:19:47.920
<i>where his legendary boat</i>
<i>sank long ago.</i>

395
00:19:48.285 --> 00:19:50.887
<i>but I had a feeling</i>
<i>we were rowing into a trap.</i>

396
00:19:51.253 --> 00:19:54.253
-Grandfather said never go
past the shoulder of Gaya.

397
00:19:54.419 --> 00:19:55.385
[bell ringing]

398
00:19:55.553 --> 00:19:56.653
-I wonder why.

399
00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:58.219
[bell rings]

400
00:19:58.385 --> 00:20:00.486
[thunder rumbling]

401
00:20:00.653 --> 00:20:03.653
[woman humming]

402
00:20:03.820 --> 00:20:04.820
-Whoa.

403
00:20:06.385 --> 00:20:07.853
-What is this place?

404
00:20:08.787 --> 00:20:10.219
[bell rings]

405
00:20:12.687 --> 00:20:14.586
-Hey. you gotta see this.

406
00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:22.419
[suspenseful music]

407
00:20:29.687 --> 00:20:31.486
[gasps]

408
00:20:31.653 --> 00:20:32.385
You saw it. right?

409
00:20:32.553 --> 00:20:33.953
-Yeah.

410
00:20:34.318 --> 00:20:35.620
-What do you think
they were doing?

411
00:20:35.787 --> 00:20:38.252
-I don't know.
You think that was his boat?

412
00:20:38.419 --> 00:20:39.453
-Someone's here.

413
00:20:39.620 --> 00:20:40.853
Quick. grab the paddles.

414
00:20:41.218 --> 00:20:43.787
[ominous music]

415
00:20:43.953 --> 00:20:47.553
[water splashing]

416
00:20:59.285 --> 00:21:01.520
-What are you doing in my bay?

417
00:21:03.620 --> 00:21:05.653
-Our boat ran dry.

418
00:21:08.720 --> 00:21:10.953
-We'll leave.
Come on.

419
00:21:12.185 --> 00:21:13.520
-Is this torpedo yours?

420
00:21:15.787 --> 00:21:17.753
It's a hydrocat.

421
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.520
-What do you know
about hydrocats?

422
00:21:20.687 --> 00:21:22.420
-My dad was in the league.

423
00:21:22.586 --> 00:21:24.385
-Mm.

424
00:21:24.553 --> 00:21:25.887
Who's his sponsor?

425
00:21:28.318 --> 00:21:30.787
-Can you help us get home?

426
00:21:30.953 --> 00:21:32.352
-Where's home?

427
00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:33.853
-We shouldn't take
a ride from her.

428
00:21:34.218 --> 00:21:36.486
-Why not?
What's wrong with me?

429
00:21:36.653 --> 00:21:38.386
-I know who you are.

430
00:21:38.553 --> 00:21:40.520
My grandfather
warned me about you.

431
00:21:43.386 --> 00:21:46.887
-[sniffs]
Fig.

432
00:21:47.252 --> 00:21:49.453
-Fig Island.

433
00:21:49.620 --> 00:21:51.553
The island of rebel riders

434
00:21:51.720 --> 00:21:54.453
who tried to break through
the storm.

435
00:21:54.620 --> 00:21:56.653
-What are you doing out here?

436
00:21:56.820 --> 00:22:00.887
-I'm looking for a boy
who's been touched by the storm.

437
00:22:01.252 --> 00:22:04.520
[suspenseful music]

438
00:22:09.920 --> 00:22:13.218
-What's it like
inside the walls?

439
00:22:13.386 --> 00:22:17.586
-I wish I could say life
on the islands was no different.

440
00:22:17.753 --> 00:22:19.753
but I wouldn't lie to you.

441
00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:23.453
There's a reason why Argos
is under population control.

442
00:22:23.620 --> 00:22:27.486
a reason
why every place must be won.

443
00:22:27.653 --> 00:22:30.687
Storm Horizon will not hold back
the wave forever.

444
00:22:31.920 --> 00:22:33.787
-Well. the storm isn't real.
ma'am.

445
00:22:35.185 --> 00:22:36.920
-Is that what your grandfather
told you?

446
00:22:40.653 --> 00:22:41.920
[box clicks]

447
00:22:42.285 --> 00:22:44.486
-They say those touched
by the storm

448
00:22:44.653 --> 00:22:47.185
can see
through the cracks of time

449
00:22:47.353 --> 00:22:50.285
and the destinies
are revealed to them.

450
00:22:50.453 --> 00:22:52.787
[screams]

451
00:22:54.153 --> 00:22:56.753
-He's just scared of the storm.

452
00:22:56.920 --> 00:22:59.218
-Yes. well. his fear...

453
00:23:00.853 --> 00:23:04.185
...is too beautiful
for you to understand.

454
00:23:05.285 --> 00:23:07.353
too powerful to tame.

455
00:23:09.687 --> 00:23:14.453
But if he confronts it.
it will make all the difference.

456
00:23:14.620 --> 00:23:17.185
[thunder rumbles]

457
00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:23.353
[men chanting]

458
00:23:23.520 --> 00:23:27.520
[ominous music]

459
00:23:27.687 --> 00:23:30.787
[footsteps approaching]

460
00:23:30.953 --> 00:23:32.620
-Still nothing.

461
00:23:32.787 --> 00:23:33.918
In the Bay of Gaya.

462
00:23:33.920 --> 00:23:35.653
all the Baroness found there
was a couple of kids.

463
00:23:36.887 --> 00:23:38.353
-Do you trust her?

464
00:23:39.653 --> 00:23:40.953
[sighs]

465
00:23:41.319 --> 00:23:43.553
-From now on.
my spies follow her too.

466
00:23:47.253 --> 00:23:51.218
[suspenseful music]

467
00:24:00.553 --> 00:24:03.286
-She said.
when the day comes

468
00:24:03.453 --> 00:24:06.653
and we need a sponsor.
she can help.

469
00:24:06.820 --> 00:24:10.920
[suspenseful music continues]

470
00:24:17.420 --> 00:24:22.253
-He's a Storm Rider.
not a farm boy.

471
00:24:25.219 --> 00:24:27.185
-Is it true?

472
00:24:27.353 --> 00:24:30.553
That the Founders
came from beyond the storm?

473
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:32.753
-Is that what she told you?

474
00:24:32.920 --> 00:24:35.620
-That's what Neb said.

475
00:24:35.787 --> 00:24:39.953
-I wonder
where he got that from.

476
00:24:40.319 --> 00:24:43.853
-So you don't believe
that Hammerhead will save us?

477
00:24:44.219 --> 00:24:47.953
-Um-hmm.
Well. I choose my myths wisely.

478
00:24:48.319 --> 00:24:50.353
-Then what is beyond
the Storm Horizon?

479
00:24:50.520 --> 00:24:52.853
[gentle music]

480
00:24:53.219 --> 00:24:55.453
-The truth.

481
00:24:55.620 --> 00:24:59.820
The Founders' greatest trick
was to convince the Islanders.

482
00:25:00.186 --> 00:25:01.853
their land was worthless.

483
00:25:02.219 --> 00:25:04.420
-What good is your land
if its days are numbered?

484
00:25:05.386 --> 00:25:07.952
-[scoffs]
Well. it's like saying.

485
00:25:08.319 --> 00:25:11.386
"What good is your life
if your days are numbered?"

486
00:25:11.553 --> 00:25:14.353
[birds chirping]

487
00:25:14.520 --> 00:25:16.753
-Neb keeps saying
there's a Titan

488
00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:18.286
living in this tree.

489
00:25:18.453 --> 00:25:22.520
-Yes.
The last Titan. Sykeus.

490
00:25:22.687 --> 00:25:25.186
[laughs]

491
00:25:25.353 --> 00:25:29.919
I planted this tree
the day Neb was born.

492
00:25:33.186 --> 00:25:35.586
So they have a special bond.

493
00:25:35.753 --> 00:25:37.353
-Its soul healed my eyes.

494
00:25:38.720 --> 00:25:40.653
-You mean
it made you see things.

495
00:25:43.453 --> 00:25:44.653
[ominous music]

496
00:25:44.820 --> 00:25:45.418
[water splashing]

497
00:25:45.420 --> 00:25:49.453
[church bell ringing]

498
00:25:56.952 --> 00:25:59.253
-Have you finished
replicating the key?

499
00:26:00.586 --> 00:26:02.787
-Yes. Lord Tarus.

500
00:26:09.286 --> 00:26:10.520
[object clicks]

501
00:26:12.386 --> 00:26:14.553
<i>-They want the storm?</i>

502
00:26:14.720 --> 00:26:16.820
<i>I will bring the storm to them.</i>

503
00:26:18.486 --> 00:26:20.286
-[Automated voice]
<i>Remote connection activated.</i>

504
00:26:20.453 --> 00:26:22.286
[machine beeping]

505
00:26:27.586 --> 00:26:29.553
[machine whirring]

506
00:26:35.420 --> 00:26:36.418
[machine buzzing]

507
00:26:36.420 --> 00:26:37.553
-[Automated voice]
<i>Remote connection lost.</i>

508
00:26:46.620 --> 00:26:47.919
[object clicks]

509
00:26:57.319 --> 00:26:58.319
[object clanks]

510
00:26:59.253 --> 00:27:01.186
-I'm sorry. my lord.

511
00:27:01.919 --> 00:27:03.219
Please.

512
00:27:03.386 --> 00:27:06.852
-You said it would work.
but it didn't.

513
00:27:07.219 --> 00:27:09.720
So you lied to me.

514
00:27:09.886 --> 00:27:11.520
[ominous music]

515
00:27:11.687 --> 00:27:16.553
[tense music]

516
00:27:16.720 --> 00:27:19.620
-Throw yourself from the wall.

517
00:27:19.787 --> 00:27:22.919
[screaming]

518
00:27:23.286 --> 00:27:24.420
[metal thumps]

519
00:27:29.386 --> 00:27:35.420
[suspenseful music]

520
00:27:35.586 --> 00:27:38.620
-[The Baroness] <i>I have seen</i>
<i>a rider enter the storm.</i>

521
00:27:38.787 --> 00:27:42.453
[voice echoing]

522
00:27:43.753 --> 00:27:46.353
[ominous music]

523
00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:48.753
[box clicks open]

524
00:27:50.687 --> 00:27:52.786
-Is it true?

525
00:27:52.952 --> 00:27:54.753
-Is what true?

526
00:27:54.919 --> 00:27:56.720
-That you can see
into the future?

527
00:27:56.886 --> 00:28:00.720
[bird and insects chirping]

528
00:28:00.886 --> 00:28:02.553
-I don't really
know what I see.

529
00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:08.353
[seagull squawking]

530
00:28:12.520 --> 00:28:16.553
Sometimes I wake up
in a different place.

531
00:28:17.786 --> 00:28:19.520
-[Neb] <i>Over the years. I watched</i>
<i>the girl from my island</i>

532
00:28:19.687 --> 00:28:21.586
<i>break and rise again.</i>

533
00:28:21.752 --> 00:28:24.219
<i>My pain for her</i>
<i>became something else.</i>

534
00:28:25.286 --> 00:28:26.919
<i>Love.</i>

535
00:28:27.286 --> 00:28:30.486
<i>the kind worth fighting for.</i>
<i>the kind worth dying for.</i>

536
00:28:30.653 --> 00:28:36.219
[sentimental music]

537
00:28:37.952 --> 00:28:39.520
[stone thumps softly]

538
00:28:40.687 --> 00:28:42.486
-Did you see that coming?

539
00:28:42.653 --> 00:28:43.819
-No.

540
00:28:45.319 --> 00:28:47.553
-What can you really see?

541
00:28:47.720 --> 00:28:48.687
-Images.

542
00:28:50.186 --> 00:28:51.653
Fragments. really.

543
00:28:52.687 --> 00:28:54.919
Like pieces in a puzzle.

544
00:28:55.286 --> 00:28:57.219
-Am I one of those pieces?

545
00:29:02.486 --> 00:29:04.553
-Yeah.
You are.

546
00:29:14.420 --> 00:29:15.920
I saw you standing

547
00:29:17.386 --> 00:29:21.286
on the shoulder of Gaya wearing
this beautiful red dress.

548
00:29:22.586 --> 00:29:24.253
-Now I know you're crazy.

549
00:29:25.686 --> 00:29:27.586
Like I'd ever wear a dress.

550
00:29:31.319 --> 00:29:32.486
Look.

551
00:29:34.286 --> 00:29:35.852
When we're out there.

552
00:29:37.420 --> 00:29:39.386
you have to ride the storm
not for me.

553
00:29:40.819 --> 00:29:41.852
For you.

554
00:29:42.786 --> 00:29:43.852
-I know.

555
00:29:45.286 --> 00:29:46.819
I just want us to be together.

556
00:29:47.786 --> 00:29:51.219
Here. there.

557
00:29:54.286 --> 00:29:55.486
I don't care.

558
00:29:58.553 --> 00:29:59.887
-I have to tell you something.

559
00:30:11.786 --> 00:30:12.786
-You promise?

560
00:30:13.786 --> 00:30:14.953
-I promise.

561
00:30:27.719 --> 00:30:28.786
[engine starts]

562
00:30:28.953 --> 00:30:30.553
[machine whirring]

563
00:30:30.719 --> 00:30:34.186
[engine humming]

564
00:30:45.486 --> 00:30:48.286
[wind blowing

565
00:30:50.386 --> 00:30:51.520
-She's gonna do it.

566
00:30:52.553 --> 00:30:53.786
-Do what?

567
00:30:53.953 --> 00:30:55.286
-Win a place.

568
00:30:57.253 --> 00:30:58.553
-So?

569
00:31:00.553 --> 00:31:01.520
-I'm afraid to lose her.

570
00:31:03.319 --> 00:31:06.920
[insects chirping]

571
00:31:18.752 --> 00:31:19.920
[groans]

572
00:31:26.619 --> 00:31:27.920
What did you see?

573
00:31:34.719 --> 00:31:35.953
Go on.

574
00:31:39.219 --> 00:31:43.319
[wind blowing]

575
00:31:43.486 --> 00:31:44.453
Neb.

576
00:31:45.686 --> 00:31:48.219
Neb. what else did you see?

577
00:31:48.386 --> 00:31:50.752
[suspenseful music]

578
00:31:50.920 --> 00:31:52.486
What did you see?

579
00:31:56.520 --> 00:31:59.686
[thunder rumbling]

580
00:31:59.853 --> 00:32:05.386
[ominous music]

581
00:32:07.753 --> 00:32:12.552
[dramatic music]

582
00:32:20.186 --> 00:32:21.820
[water splashing]

583
00:32:24.486 --> 00:32:26.853
[lightning static]

584
00:32:32.519 --> 00:32:34.753
[ominous music]

585
00:32:34.920 --> 00:32:37.686
-[Neb] <i>I saw Ana in the race.</i>
<i>chasing the storm.</i>

586
00:32:37.853 --> 00:32:40.386
<i>trying to fulfill her pledge</i>
<i>and avenge her father.</i>

587
00:32:40.552 --> 00:32:41.652
-Neb!

588
00:32:42.686 --> 00:32:45.186
Neb!
What are you doing?

589
00:32:45.353 --> 00:32:46.652
[thunder rumbles]

590
00:32:46.820 --> 00:32:48.253
Come on. boy!

591
00:32:48.420 --> 00:32:51.386
-[Neb] <i>But in the end. she fell.</i>

592
00:32:52.386 --> 00:32:54.787
-Get inside.
Come on!

593
00:32:56.253 --> 00:32:58.853
-[Neb] <i>The Baroness came back</i>
<i>like she said she would.</i>

594
00:32:59.219 --> 00:33:01.619
<i>trying to settle</i>
<i>their old score.</i>

595
00:33:01.787 --> 00:33:04.953
<i>She hides a dark secret</i>
<i>behind those glasses.</i>

596
00:33:05.319 --> 00:33:07.552
<i>Grandfather doesn't trust her.</i>

597
00:33:07.720 --> 00:33:12.286
-A quiet life
on a quiet little island.

598
00:33:12.453 --> 00:33:14.319
[spits]

599
00:33:14.485 --> 00:33:17.319
-And you still have
an attitude problem.

600
00:33:17.485 --> 00:33:20.652
-People have a problem
with my attitude.

601
00:33:20.820 --> 00:33:22.585
[suspenseful music]

602
00:33:22.753 --> 00:33:25.353
-The Founders are searching
for what you have.

603
00:33:26.452 --> 00:33:28.386
But I can see
you're not using it.

604
00:33:28.552 --> 00:33:31.386
-The boy doesn't want to ride.

605
00:33:31.552 --> 00:33:32.753
-But his friend does.

606
00:33:33.953 --> 00:33:35.820
And she took me up on it.

607
00:33:36.186 --> 00:33:39.253
-The wolf has a right
to the sheep.

608
00:33:39.420 --> 00:33:42.787
-I can't change the past.

609
00:33:42.953 --> 00:33:44.653
-And neither can he.

610
00:33:44.820 --> 00:33:49.353
Because what you ask
cannot be done. Baroness.

611
00:33:49.519 --> 00:33:53.319
-Then let's give a chance
for fate to intervene.

612
00:33:55.386 --> 00:33:56.787
-Is this what you want?

613
00:33:57.853 --> 00:34:01.585
To ride for the Founders?
They are not who they seem.

614
00:34:02.853 --> 00:34:06.253
They have been picking off
island after island.

615
00:34:06.419 --> 00:34:07.787
devouring the land.

616
00:34:09.386 --> 00:34:12.787
because they are getting older
faster than they wish.

617
00:34:13.853 --> 00:34:18.186
-My dear old man.
you're missing the point.

618
00:34:18.353 --> 00:34:22.787
It's about the boy
who wants to follow the girl.

619
00:34:22.953 --> 00:34:25.286
I'm just here to help.

620
00:34:25.452 --> 00:34:31.219
Besides. you had your chance
ages ago. old friend.

621
00:34:33.787 --> 00:34:36.485
My sponsorship
is good for a year.

622
00:34:38.319 --> 00:34:41.452
The good people
of Fig Island need a champion.

623
00:34:41.620 --> 00:34:43.820
But I expect much more from you.

624
00:34:46.419 --> 00:34:49.753
[wind blowing]

625
00:34:56.519 --> 00:34:57.953
-[Neb] <i>The Landless Sea.</i>

626
00:34:58.319 --> 00:34:59.383
<i>the Founders' death race</i>

627
00:34:59.385 --> 00:35:01.953
<i>has left countless Islanders</i>
<i>without homes.</i>

628
00:35:02.319 --> 00:35:05.385
[women chanting]

629
00:35:05.552 --> 00:35:07.653
<i>Condemned to the mercy</i>
<i>of the deep sea.</i>

630
00:35:07.820 --> 00:35:10.485
<i>no land. no shelter.</i>

631
00:35:10.653 --> 00:35:13.920
<i>Generations born on boats.</i>
<i>raised by the waves.</i>

632
00:35:14.286 --> 00:35:16.519
<i>Never knowing the feel</i>
<i>of solid ground.</i>

633
00:35:16.687 --> 00:35:19.787
<i>Their only hope. Hammerhead.</i>

634
00:35:19.953 --> 00:35:21.853
-What are those green
on those rocks?

635
00:35:22.219 --> 00:35:24.553
[bomb explodes]

636
00:35:24.720 --> 00:35:27.452
-Islanders call them trees.

637
00:35:30.519 --> 00:35:33.920
[bombs exploding]

638
00:35:35.385 --> 00:35:37.419
-Why are they doing this?

639
00:35:39.318 --> 00:35:42.154
-Only the Founders know why.

640
00:35:42.352 --> 00:35:46.787
[indistinct distant
conversation]

641
00:35:46.953 --> 00:35:50.519
[exploding continues]

642
00:35:50.687 --> 00:35:51.653
-Lady.

643
00:35:52.687 --> 00:35:54.820
They ask tough questions.

644
00:35:56.720 --> 00:36:00.253
My son is waterborne too.

645
00:36:00.419 --> 00:36:01.618
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>Let's also note</i>

646
00:36:01.620 --> 00:36:03.787
that the island of <i>[indistinct]</i>
<i>had a close encounter</i>

647
00:36:03.953 --> 00:36:05.586
<i>with a storm earlier this month.</i>

648
00:36:05.753 --> 00:36:07.419
<i>and that their residents</i>
<i>put all faith</i>

649
00:36:07.586 --> 00:36:08.953
<i>in their selected champions</i>

650
00:36:09.318 --> 00:36:11.285
<i>to represent their hope</i>
<i>for their safety</i>

651
00:36:11.452 --> 00:36:12.818
<i>in the upcoming cycle.</i>

652
00:36:12.820 --> 00:36:15.887
<i>In racing news. we are excited</i>
<i>to announce that three islands</i>

653
00:36:16.253 --> 00:36:18.586
<i>have been selected</i>
<i>for the next cycle.</i>

654
00:36:18.753 --> 00:36:21.887
<i>Congratulations to the island</i>
<i>of Crater. [indistinct] Rose</i>

655
00:36:22.253 --> 00:36:23.253
<i>and making a comeback...</i>

656
00:36:23.419 --> 00:36:24.417
-Give me a 10.

657
00:36:24.419 --> 00:36:25.217
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>...after a ten-year ban.</i>

658
00:36:25.219 --> 00:36:26.853
<i>the tiny Fig Island.</i>

659
00:36:27.219 --> 00:36:28.251
<i>From weather-related news...</i>

660
00:36:28.253 --> 00:36:31.285
-You'll have to watch
for this right flank.

661
00:36:31.452 --> 00:36:33.853
It's not as straight
as it should be.

662
00:36:34.219 --> 00:36:36.687
but don't compromise
your back too much.

663
00:36:36.853 --> 00:36:38.753
Use your knees.

664
00:36:38.920 --> 00:36:40.385
-[Radio Announcer] <i>It's been</i>
<i>ten years since Fig Island</i>

665
00:36:40.553 --> 00:36:42.586
<i>last had competitors</i>
<i>in the race.</i>

666
00:36:42.753 --> 00:36:44.486
<i>One must hope</i>
<i>they've learned their lesson</i>

667
00:36:44.653 --> 00:36:45.618
<i>and that no treachery</i>

668
00:36:45.620 --> 00:36:47.787
<i>will be displayed</i>
<i>this time around.</i>

669
00:36:47.953 --> 00:36:49.553
-The storm took your mother.

670
00:36:50.787 --> 00:36:52.219
It took my father.

671
00:36:53.385 --> 00:36:55.787
How many Islanders
does it take?

672
00:36:55.953 --> 00:37:00.787
[somber music]

673
00:37:00.953 --> 00:37:02.687
I have to find out
the truth. Neb.

674
00:37:06.219 --> 00:37:07.620
I have to.

675
00:37:12.486 --> 00:37:15.787
[tense music]

676
00:37:30.853 --> 00:37:33.186
-[Neb] <i>I know Ana wants</i>
<i>to break through the storm.</i>

677
00:37:33.352 --> 00:37:35.352
<i>but I also know</i>
<i>it's a suicidal mission.</i>

678
00:37:36.553 --> 00:37:39.285
<i>I'll stay by her side.</i>
<i>protect her.</i>

679
00:37:39.453 --> 00:37:40.820
<i>and take her place in death.</i>

680
00:37:42.252 --> 00:37:43.453
[church bell rings]

681
00:37:45.420 --> 00:37:48.753
[suspenseful music]

682
00:37:57.453 --> 00:38:00.185
[suspenseful music fades]

683
00:38:00.352 --> 00:38:01.586
-You all know the rules.

684
00:38:01.753 --> 00:38:04.352
Two riders per island.
two legs in the cycle.

685
00:38:04.520 --> 00:38:07.385
The team with the most points
wins the place inside the walls

686
00:38:07.553 --> 00:38:08.853
for their home island.

687
00:38:09.218 --> 00:38:11.453
You finish last.
and the people from your island

688
00:38:11.620 --> 00:38:13.486
will be cast out to open sea.

689
00:38:13.653 --> 00:38:16.653
The start and finish line
are between the ancient statues

690
00:38:16.820 --> 00:38:18.820
just outside the city gates.

691
00:38:19.185 --> 00:38:21.218
The course runs through
the natural canal

692
00:38:21.386 --> 00:38:23.285
all the way out to the edge
of the Storm Horizon

693
00:38:23.453 --> 00:38:24.553
by Neptune's Rock.

694
00:38:24.720 --> 00:38:26.887
That is your midpoint.

695
00:38:27.252 --> 00:38:33.185
Beyond this point.
your compass will be useless

696
00:38:33.352 --> 00:38:37.720
and you'll be fighting inertia
unlike any you ever felt.

697
00:38:39.486 --> 00:38:43.620
So the last thing you want
is to be dragged into the storm

698
00:38:43.787 --> 00:38:45.920
because no one.
listen carefully.

699
00:38:46.285 --> 00:38:49.787
no one survives the storm.

700
00:38:50.953 --> 00:38:52.453
-You saw that. right?

701
00:38:53.820 --> 00:38:55.353
-It's not about winning.

702
00:38:56.953 --> 00:38:58.420
it's about surviving.

703
00:38:59.586 --> 00:39:02.486
[footsteps approaching]

704
00:39:03.553 --> 00:39:04.620
-Kneel.

705
00:39:08.853 --> 00:39:10.553
-What human do you bring?

706
00:39:11.687 --> 00:39:13.920
-He is the most ruthless rider
I ever trained.

707
00:39:15.285 --> 00:39:16.887
-Where are you from. servant?

708
00:39:17.252 --> 00:39:18.553
-Speak.

709
00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:21.252
-The island of Bacchus. my lord.

710
00:39:22.553 --> 00:39:25.520
-The pagans there still hold
faith in Gaya. do they not?

711
00:39:26.653 --> 00:39:29.553
-The pagan chief promised
she would save us.

712
00:39:29.720 --> 00:39:33.353
But still. the storm came and--

713
00:39:34.920 --> 00:39:36.218
-Tell me.

714
00:39:37.486 --> 00:39:40.820
-The storm. the wrath of Gaya.

715
00:39:42.386 --> 00:39:45.353
dragged their souls
to the bottom of the sea.

716
00:39:46.553 --> 00:39:50.386
-Now you know Gaya never saves.

717
00:39:51.520 --> 00:39:52.820
She only punishes.

718
00:39:54.953 --> 00:39:57.420
-I shall drown
the pagan believers

719
00:39:58.486 --> 00:40:00.920
like that storm did
to my family.

720
00:40:01.286 --> 00:40:05.218
[ominous music]

721
00:40:05.386 --> 00:40:10.520
-[Neb] <i>Bombheads.</i>
<i>Tarus's watchdogs and assassins.</i>

722
00:40:10.687 --> 00:40:13.386
[men chanting]

723
00:40:13.553 --> 00:40:15.252
-Rise.

724
00:40:15.420 --> 00:40:16.753
You will start
with Baroness's riders

725
00:40:16.920 --> 00:40:18.720
on Fig Island.

726
00:40:18.887 --> 00:40:23.319
And everyone who serves me
above all must always...

727
00:40:23.486 --> 00:40:25.453
-Always protect the storm.

728
00:40:25.620 --> 00:40:27.253
[tense music]

729
00:40:27.420 --> 00:40:28.420
-No. I'm not listening. Ana.

730
00:40:28.586 --> 00:40:30.787
-Look. we do this now.

731
00:40:32.420 --> 00:40:34.218
We--we break through the storm

732
00:40:35.353 --> 00:40:37.753
and no Islander
will ever have to race again.

733
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:40.420
-You...

734
00:40:40.586 --> 00:40:41.687
I can't protect you out there.

735
00:40:41.853 --> 00:40:43.486
-I don't need your protection.

736
00:40:45.286 --> 00:40:46.753
The visions that plague you...

737
00:40:49.586 --> 00:40:51.753
do not guarantee an outcome.

738
00:40:52.820 --> 00:40:54.420
-That's what I hope.

739
00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:58.853
-So. will you come with me
or are you gonna be no fun?

740
00:40:59.219 --> 00:41:00.687
-[scoffs]
Like I'd have a chance.

741
00:41:01.787 --> 00:41:02.920
-Promise?

742
00:41:03.920 --> 00:41:05.319
-I promise.

743
00:41:06.653 --> 00:41:07.953
-There are no guarantees.

744
00:41:10.787 --> 00:41:12.720
Not in life. not in love.

745
00:41:18.586 --> 00:41:20.753
And I wouldn't want it
any other way.

746
00:41:23.820 --> 00:41:29.653
[somber music]

747
00:41:29.820 --> 00:41:33.553
-[Neb] <i>Promises were made.</i>
<i>Promises must be kept.</i>

748
00:41:33.720 --> 00:41:35.286
[audience cheering]

749
00:41:35.453 --> 00:41:36.687
[engine whirring]

750
00:41:39.353 --> 00:41:41.186
[engine humming]

751
00:41:41.353 --> 00:41:45.286
-[Race Announcer] <i>Five.</i>
four. three. two. one.

752
00:41:45.453 --> 00:41:47.720
[speed accelerator clanks]

753
00:41:47.887 --> 00:41:49.284
<i>And they're off.</i>

754
00:41:49.286 --> 00:41:51.386
<i>It is an aggressive start</i>
<i>for Fig Island riders</i>

755
00:41:51.553 --> 00:41:53.453
<i>as they immediately</i>
<i>take the lead.</i>

756
00:41:53.620 --> 00:41:55.586
<i>They seem quite aware</i>
<i>that this is their last chance</i>

757
00:41:55.753 --> 00:41:57.486
<i>to control their future</i>
<i>and make amends</i>

758
00:41:57.653 --> 00:41:59.520
<i>for their island's</i>
<i>controversial past.</i>

759
00:41:59.687 --> 00:42:02.453
[machine whirring]

760
00:42:04.253 --> 00:42:08.453
[tense music]

761
00:42:11.453 --> 00:42:13.553
<i>From the outside.</i>
<i>Viking [indistinct] riders</i>

762
00:42:13.720 --> 00:42:15.286
<i>picks up speed</i>
<i>to overtake the position.</i>

763
00:42:15.453 --> 00:42:17.853
[audience applauding]

764
00:42:18.219 --> 00:42:19.687
[water splashing]

765
00:42:19.853 --> 00:42:22.219
[tense music continues]

766
00:42:22.386 --> 00:42:24.620
[engine humming]

767
00:42:27.453 --> 00:42:29.353
[water splashing]

768
00:42:34.486 --> 00:42:36.453
[intense music]

769
00:42:36.620 --> 00:42:38.486
[machine whirring]

770
00:42:40.952 --> 00:42:44.886
[tense music]

771
00:42:47.952 --> 00:42:49.319
[machine whirring]

772
00:42:51.886 --> 00:42:53.386
[water splashes]

773
00:42:58.952 --> 00:43:00.853
[engine humming]

774
00:43:01.720 --> 00:43:03.553
[machine whirring]

775
00:43:05.286 --> 00:43:10.253
[tense music]

776
00:43:13.286 --> 00:43:14.886
<i>The rider from Crater cuts</i>
<i>in from the outside.</i>

777
00:43:15.253 --> 00:43:17.319
<i>fighting inertia as they</i>
<i>approach the Neptune's Rock</i>

778
00:43:17.486 --> 00:43:18.919
<i>and prepare to the final stretch</i>

779
00:43:19.286 --> 00:43:20.852
<i>with Fig Island</i>
<i>still in the lead.</i>

780
00:43:21.219 --> 00:43:22.253
<i>She's on tail!</i>

781
00:43:22.420 --> 00:43:25.453
[suspenseful music]

782
00:43:27.286 --> 00:43:28.753
[engine humming]

783
00:43:34.253 --> 00:43:35.852
[water splashes]

784
00:43:36.219 --> 00:43:38.319
<i>The power of lightning</i>
<i>slashes Crater rider in half.</i>

785
00:43:38.486 --> 00:43:39.852
<i>blowing pieces</i>
<i>of the shot [indistinct]</i>

786
00:43:40.219 --> 00:43:41.687
<i>barely missed</i>
<i>the riders from Fig.</i>

787
00:43:41.852 --> 00:43:43.386
[audience applauding]

788
00:43:43.553 --> 00:43:47.620
[tense music]

789
00:43:52.819 --> 00:43:54.819
[engine humming]

790
00:43:55.186 --> 00:43:58.653
[tense music continues]

791
00:44:02.520 --> 00:44:05.486
[thunder rumbling]

792
00:44:10.486 --> 00:44:13.787
<i>Oh. no. the front runner</i>
<i>from Fig Island breaks off.</i>

793
00:44:13.952 --> 00:44:15.520
<i>She is on the loose.</i>

794
00:44:15.687 --> 00:44:17.486
<i>As we witness history repeating.</i>

795
00:44:17.653 --> 00:44:19.919
<i>the Fig Island rider is heading</i>
<i>towards certain death.</i>

796
00:44:21.420 --> 00:44:22.919
<i>Argos rider is hot on her tail.</i>

797
00:44:23.286 --> 00:44:25.253
<i>This behavior</i>
<i>will not be tolerated.</i>

798
00:44:25.420 --> 00:44:27.453
<i>All rebel riders</i>
<i>must be stopped.</i>

799
00:44:27.620 --> 00:44:30.253
<i>These insolent provocations</i>
<i>must be punished!</i>

800
00:44:32.553 --> 00:44:34.319
[engine humming]

801
00:44:35.687 --> 00:44:37.786
[machine whirring]

802
00:44:37.952 --> 00:44:39.720
[water splashing]

803
00:44:40.486 --> 00:44:44.186
[tense music]

804
00:44:45.786 --> 00:44:49.353
[thunder rumbles]

805
00:44:59.720 --> 00:45:02.952
[suspenseful music]

806
00:45:03.319 --> 00:45:04.752
[thunder rumbles]

807
00:45:11.553 --> 00:45:15.886
[men chanting]

808
00:45:16.253 --> 00:45:18.553
[tense music]

809
00:45:42.520 --> 00:45:47.486
[lightning static]

810
00:45:54.620 --> 00:45:56.687
[thunder rumbling]

811
00:45:59.353 --> 00:46:04.553
[somber music]

812
00:46:08.920 --> 00:46:11.186
[engine humming]

813
00:46:14.886 --> 00:46:16.253
[machine whirring]

814
00:46:17.920 --> 00:46:20.786
[tense music]

815
00:46:27.786 --> 00:46:29.319
[thunder rumbling]

816
00:46:30.353 --> 00:46:31.353
[boat crashes]

817
00:46:31.520 --> 00:46:32.953
[water splashes]

818
00:46:33.319 --> 00:46:34.852
<i>Swift punishment</i>
<i>for the rebel rider of Fig.</i>

819
00:46:35.219 --> 00:46:37.219
<i>by the protectors of the storm.</i>

820
00:46:37.386 --> 00:46:41.186
<i>Per decree of Argos.</i>
<i>no one survives the storm.</i>

821
00:46:41.353 --> 00:46:42.686
[thunder rumbling]

822
00:46:46.953 --> 00:46:48.253
[water splashes]

823
00:46:49.420 --> 00:46:50.920
[engine humming]

824
00:46:58.253 --> 00:47:02.353
[tense music fades]

825
00:47:07.620 --> 00:47:12.586
[somber music]

826
00:47:43.286 --> 00:47:44.386
[water splashes]

827
00:47:44.553 --> 00:47:45.652
[gasps]

828
00:47:47.786 --> 00:47:51.920
[panting]

829
00:47:52.286 --> 00:47:53.920
<i>The second Storm Rider</i>
<i>from Crater wins this one</i>

830
00:47:54.286 --> 00:47:55.317
<i>for his home island.</i>

831
00:47:55.319 --> 00:47:56.953
<i>raising hopes</i>
<i>for their Argos residents</i>

832
00:47:57.319 --> 00:47:59.286
<i>in the second leg of the cycle.</i>

833
00:48:00.953 --> 00:48:03.420
[thunder rumbles]

834
00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:10.820
[ominous music]

835
00:48:11.186 --> 00:48:13.453
<i>But the real story</i>
<i>of the day is Fig Island.</i>

836
00:48:13.619 --> 00:48:15.286
<i>who will most likely</i>
<i>in a week's time.</i>

837
00:48:15.453 --> 00:48:16.787
<i>be heading for the open sea.</i>

838
00:48:16.953 --> 00:48:19.652
[ominous music fades]

839
00:48:21.853 --> 00:48:22.887
-[Neb] <i>Guilt.</i>

840
00:48:24.953 --> 00:48:26.719
<i>An internal prison cell.</i>

841
00:48:26.887 --> 00:48:28.652
[thunder rumbles]

842
00:48:28.820 --> 00:48:30.619
<i>Visions blur with memories.</i>

843
00:48:31.652 --> 00:48:33.585
<i>Nothing feels real anymore.</i>

844
00:48:33.752 --> 00:48:35.652
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>Per decree of Argos.</i>

845
00:48:35.820 --> 00:48:38.286
<i>no one survives the storm.</i>

846
00:48:38.453 --> 00:48:42.652
[water splashing softly]

847
00:48:44.552 --> 00:48:45.920
[door opens]

848
00:48:47.820 --> 00:48:49.552
[door shuts]

849
00:48:51.585 --> 00:48:54.619
[footsteps approaching]

850
00:49:05.486 --> 00:49:07.186
-I knew a boy like you once.

851
00:49:09.353 --> 00:49:14.420
An islander who'd do anything
to save his land.

852
00:49:17.486 --> 00:49:22.887
Push himself to win.
no matter what the cost.

853
00:49:25.286 --> 00:49:30.519
even if that meant
that no one else would ever win.

854
00:49:30.686 --> 00:49:34.787
[ominous music]

855
00:49:49.253 --> 00:49:51.386
I wore that helmet. kid.

856
00:49:54.453 --> 00:49:56.953
I rode for Tarus once.

857
00:49:57.319 --> 00:49:58.953
-What about all the people
from the island?

858
00:49:59.953 --> 00:50:01.319
The people you saved.

859
00:50:05.552 --> 00:50:07.452
-They never needed saving.

860
00:50:11.219 --> 00:50:11.951
[door opens]

861
00:50:11.953 --> 00:50:13.753
The Baroness wants to see you.

862
00:50:19.652 --> 00:50:23.853
[suspenseful music]

863
00:50:36.219 --> 00:50:37.485
-How is your back?

864
00:50:38.619 --> 00:50:39.920
-It'll get better.

865
00:50:41.419 --> 00:50:42.787
-Yes. it will.

866
00:50:44.219 --> 00:50:46.186
-I won't let you
take our island.

867
00:50:47.253 --> 00:50:49.820
You still think this
is about your island?

868
00:50:51.552 --> 00:50:54.253
Well. let me save you
the suspense;

869
00:50:54.419 --> 00:50:55.620
it's not.

870
00:50:55.787 --> 00:50:58.787
You see. Neb.
many years ago.

871
00:50:58.953 --> 00:51:01.452
after our world was drowned.

872
00:51:01.620 --> 00:51:04.219
the members of Operation Titan

873
00:51:04.385 --> 00:51:07.485
voyaged to this anomaly
that we call our world.

874
00:51:08.620 --> 00:51:11.452
Our mission
was to explore the oceans

875
00:51:12.720 --> 00:51:14.753
and find hope for life.

876
00:51:14.920 --> 00:51:17.219
[somber music]

877
00:51:17.385 --> 00:51:20.720
We discovered an archipelago
with hundreds of islands

878
00:51:20.887 --> 00:51:23.953
that had somehow escaped
that global destruction.

879
00:51:24.319 --> 00:51:25.219
[church bell rings]

880
00:51:25.385 --> 00:51:28.853
[woman humming]

881
00:51:29.219 --> 00:51:31.720
The Islanders we found there
believed they were protected

882
00:51:31.887 --> 00:51:33.687
by the goddess they called Gaya.

883
00:51:33.853 --> 00:51:35.286
And the Islanders had protected

884
00:51:35.452 --> 00:51:37.586
what they believed
to be Gaya's own blood.

885
00:51:38.552 --> 00:51:41.787
We called it the element.

886
00:51:43.787 --> 00:51:47.352
None of us could resist
the call of eternal life.

887
00:51:48.419 --> 00:51:51.586
And so we founded Argos.

888
00:51:51.753 --> 00:51:52.818
Tarus took the technology

889
00:51:52.820 --> 00:51:56.586
designed to protect
an endangered environment.

890
00:51:56.753 --> 00:52:00.853
but instead turned it
to entrap one so pure.

891
00:52:01.953 --> 00:52:05.419
As our campaign
of terror raged on.

892
00:52:05.586 --> 00:52:10.286
the islands were getting crushed
and drained of their element

893
00:52:10.452 --> 00:52:13.920
until one of us
finally had the strength

894
00:52:14.286 --> 00:52:15.687
to walk away.

895
00:52:16.820 --> 00:52:19.219
We knew him as Sykeus.

896
00:52:19.385 --> 00:52:20.653
[box clicks open]

897
00:52:20.820 --> 00:52:22.620
He tried to put an end to it.

898
00:52:24.787 --> 00:52:27.519
But alas. he failed.

899
00:52:28.553 --> 00:52:31.452
Exiled himself
where no one could find him

900
00:52:32.586 --> 00:52:34.820
and began to age again.

901
00:52:36.520 --> 00:52:40.687
Now. your grandfather.
he knew all that.

902
00:52:42.219 --> 00:52:44.687
His impulse
to protect you was correct.

903
00:52:45.553 --> 00:52:47.485
[chain clinking]

904
00:52:51.620 --> 00:52:54.953
Go home.
put the past behind you.

905
00:52:55.318 --> 00:52:56.920
and accept your destiny.

906
00:52:57.285 --> 00:52:58.853
You have a promise to fulfill.

907
00:53:00.219 --> 00:53:01.184
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>Bolts of lightning</i>

908
00:53:01.186 --> 00:53:03.285
<i>have demolished</i>
<i>the hilltop households</i>

909
00:53:03.452 --> 00:53:05.285
<i>of the island of Kazan</i>

910
00:53:05.452 --> 00:53:08.687
<i>with the exact number</i>
<i>of casualties still unknown.</i>

911
00:53:08.853 --> 00:53:11.586
<i>In racing news.</i>
<i>we've received confirmation</i>

912
00:53:11.753 --> 00:53:13.720
<i>that the surviving rider</i>
<i>from Fig Island</i>

913
00:53:13.887 --> 00:53:16.419
<i>is on the path</i>
<i>to a complete recovery.</i>

914
00:53:16.586 --> 00:53:17.785
<i>and is expected to return</i>

915
00:53:17.787 --> 00:53:21.385
<i>for the upcoming second</i>
<i>and final race of the cycle</i>

916
00:53:21.553 --> 00:53:22.820
<i>with the destiny of his island</i>

917
00:53:23.186 --> 00:53:25.252
<i>now resting squarely</i>
<i>on his shoulders.</i>

918
00:53:25.419 --> 00:53:28.352
[insects chirping]

919
00:53:28.520 --> 00:53:30.553
-It was just a story.
wasn't it?

920
00:53:32.553 --> 00:53:36.452
The Baroness told me
who you are. Sykeus.

921
00:53:37.753 --> 00:53:41.318
You taught me everything
about this world.

922
00:53:41.486 --> 00:53:43.687
And you lied.

923
00:53:43.853 --> 00:53:48.219
[soft tense music]

924
00:53:50.218 --> 00:53:51.385
-For protection.

925
00:53:51.553 --> 00:53:52.787
-Protect me from what?

926
00:53:52.953 --> 00:53:54.453
-The Founders.

927
00:53:54.620 --> 00:53:56.753
-Why didn't you just tell me
the truth instead?

928
00:53:59.352 --> 00:54:02.520
-It doesn't matter
where we come from.

929
00:54:04.486 --> 00:54:08.586
In the end.
we are Islanders.

930
00:54:09.787 --> 00:54:11.853
forged by the sea.

931
00:54:13.620 --> 00:54:18.453
That is all
we ever need to know.

932
00:54:19.787 --> 00:54:24.218
Till the end
of the world and back.

933
00:54:26.553 --> 00:54:28.385
-[Neb] <i>Dida tried</i>
to stand in my way.

934
00:54:28.553 --> 00:54:29.887
<i>but his eyes weren't stern.</i>

935
00:54:30.252 --> 00:54:31.350
<i>They were afraid.</i>

936
00:54:31.352 --> 00:54:33.953
<i>But it wasn't just fear.</i>
<i>it was something more.</i>

937
00:54:34.318 --> 00:54:36.953
<i>Something he wouldn't say.</i>
<i>something he knew.</i>

938
00:54:37.318 --> 00:54:38.820
<i>Yet I couldn't turn back.</i>

939
00:54:39.185 --> 00:54:40.183
<i>Not now.</i>

940
00:54:40.185 --> 00:54:42.318
<i>Not when the storm</i>
<i>was calling my name.</i>

941
00:54:44.285 --> 00:54:47.687
[somber music]

942
00:54:47.853 --> 00:54:50.218
-Neb keeps saying
there's a Titan

943
00:54:50.386 --> 00:54:51.653
living in this tree.

944
00:54:51.820 --> 00:54:55.820
-Yes. the last Titan.

945
00:54:56.185 --> 00:54:57.453
Sykeus.

946
00:54:58.520 --> 00:55:01.853
I planted this tree
the day Neb was born.

947
00:55:03.453 --> 00:55:05.486
So they have a special bond.

948
00:55:11.653 --> 00:55:13.520
[tense music]

949
00:55:13.687 --> 00:55:15.218
[wind blowing]

950
00:55:15.386 --> 00:55:16.853
[tense music fades]

951
00:55:29.252 --> 00:55:32.620
-I'm sorry. son.
I know how much you loved her.

952
00:55:37.887 --> 00:55:40.486
The day your mother died.
part of me died.

953
00:55:42.353 --> 00:55:44.720
-Did you know about
Dida's stories?

954
00:55:45.753 --> 00:55:47.687
-Which one?

955
00:55:47.853 --> 00:55:49.620
Your grandfather
has many stories.

956
00:55:49.787 --> 00:55:50.651
and it's all about the man

957
00:55:50.653 --> 00:55:53.720
who's unable
to let go of his past.

958
00:55:53.887 --> 00:55:55.520
-So you don't believe him?

959
00:55:55.687 --> 00:55:57.820
-I never wanted
to be part of his war.

960
00:56:00.887 --> 00:56:03.853
When I was young.
when storms came.

961
00:56:04.218 --> 00:56:06.252
he used to disappear
into the night.

962
00:56:06.420 --> 00:56:07.586
I never knew why.

963
00:56:08.787 --> 00:56:10.285
When I got older.

964
00:56:10.453 --> 00:56:12.753
he taught me
how to embrace lightning.

965
00:56:12.920 --> 00:56:14.720
how to become part of the storm.

966
00:56:16.252 --> 00:56:17.687
-Part of the storm?

967
00:56:17.853 --> 00:56:18.953
-Yes.

968
00:56:20.218 --> 00:56:22.687
Dida used to say
that the storm itself

969
00:56:22.853 --> 00:56:24.920
could transport you
to the other side.

970
00:56:26.853 --> 00:56:31.787
[thunder rumbles]

971
00:56:31.953 --> 00:56:33.353
In the center of the storm

972
00:56:33.520 --> 00:56:35.386
is what you kids call
the dancing bolt.

973
00:56:36.787 --> 00:56:40.386
He trained me to catch it.
but I could never do it.

974
00:56:42.453 --> 00:56:45.185
-[sighs]
Hammerhead did.

975
00:56:46.953 --> 00:56:49.486
And it dragged him
through the storm.

976
00:56:52.586 --> 00:56:54.218
I saw him. Dad.

977
00:56:55.286 --> 00:56:57.820
-Radio never mentioned
he was in the race.

978
00:56:58.185 --> 00:56:59.286
-There's a lot of things
about the race

979
00:56:59.453 --> 00:57:00.920
that the radio doesn't mention.

980
00:57:02.353 --> 00:57:05.586
That war Dida talked about.
it was never his war.

981
00:57:06.687 --> 00:57:08.687
This is our war.

982
00:57:11.420 --> 00:57:13.353
[suspenseful music]

983
00:57:17.687 --> 00:57:18.853
-It's time.

984
00:57:20.953 --> 00:57:22.353
He's ready.

985
00:57:28.553 --> 00:57:31.920
-We have to let go
of the life you planned

986
00:57:32.286 --> 00:57:36.353
in order to accept
the life that awaits.

987
00:57:36.520 --> 00:57:37.720
[box opens]

988
00:57:37.887 --> 00:57:41.253
In the old world.
they had a saying.

989
00:57:41.420 --> 00:57:43.253
"Amor fati."

990
00:57:43.420 --> 00:57:47.286
If your destiny
lays beyond the storm.

991
00:57:47.453 --> 00:57:48.787
you will need
a certain equipment

992
00:57:48.953 --> 00:57:51.253
to help you break through.

993
00:57:51.420 --> 00:57:54.386
It is kept hidden
in the Temple of Founders.

994
00:57:54.553 --> 00:57:57.887
and so is the truth
of who you are.

995
00:57:58.253 --> 00:58:00.219
[dramatic music]

996
00:58:00.386 --> 00:58:02.420
-[Neb] <i>For years.</i>
<i>Dida carried the key.</i>

997
00:58:02.586 --> 00:58:05.286
<i>hid it. feared it.</i>

998
00:58:05.453 --> 00:58:07.353
<i>Now. he passed it on to me.</i>

999
00:58:07.520 --> 00:58:11.420
<i>Not as a burden. not as a curse.</i>
<i>As a choice.</i>

1000
00:58:11.586 --> 00:58:14.386
<i>He's done hiding.</i>
<i>and so am I.</i>

1001
00:58:29.453 --> 00:58:31.219
[dramatic music fades]

1002
00:58:34.286 --> 00:58:36.787
[church bell ringing]

1003
00:58:36.952 --> 00:58:41.520
[somber music]

1004
00:58:58.919 --> 00:59:00.753
[suspenseful music]

1005
00:59:00.919 --> 00:59:04.586
-What were you doing
on the island of Rosehips?

1006
00:59:04.753 --> 00:59:07.620
-Congratulations. Lord Tarus.

1007
00:59:07.787 --> 00:59:10.620
I had no idea your spies
reached that far.

1008
00:59:12.286 --> 00:59:13.453
Crop production
on the Red Island

1009
00:59:13.620 --> 00:59:15.887
has been declining
three years in a row.

1010
00:59:16.253 --> 00:59:17.820
Your spies
didn't tell you that?

1011
00:59:19.353 --> 00:59:22.952
It's my duty to ensure
our subjects are well fed.

1012
00:59:24.286 --> 00:59:26.952
Hunger incites revolution.

1013
00:59:27.319 --> 00:59:28.553
-We wouldn't want that.

1014
00:59:29.586 --> 00:59:31.253
What actions were taken?

1015
00:59:31.420 --> 00:59:34.952
-I told them
either they increase production

1016
00:59:35.319 --> 00:59:36.919
or they become part of our wall.

1017
00:59:37.286 --> 00:59:39.787
-Do not take me for a fool.

1018
00:59:39.952 --> 00:59:43.253
Every whispered word
always finds its way back to me.

1019
00:59:49.853 --> 00:59:51.453
[ominous music]

1020
01:00:00.753 --> 01:00:05.219
[compass beeping]

1021
01:00:13.420 --> 01:00:16.687
[somber music]

1022
01:00:16.852 --> 01:00:19.620
-[Neb] <i>This isn't just a key.</i>
<i>it's a compass.</i>

1023
01:00:19.787 --> 01:00:22.453
<i>A relic from the Old world</i>
<i>guiding me to the one place</i>

1024
01:00:22.620 --> 01:00:24.952
<i>the Founders never wanted</i>
<i>anyone to find.</i>

1025
01:00:25.886 --> 01:00:28.186
<i>The answer is hidden</i>
<i>in their temple.</i>

1026
01:00:28.353 --> 01:00:31.219
<i>Heavily guarded. sealed away.</i>

1027
01:00:31.386 --> 01:00:34.819
<i>But now the path is clear.</i>
<i>and I'm going in.</i>

1028
01:00:35.186 --> 01:00:39.286
[compass beeping]

1029
01:00:42.386 --> 01:00:46.219
[compass beeping faster]

1030
01:00:50.286 --> 01:00:53.253
[compass beeps slowly]

1031
01:00:53.420 --> 01:00:56.420
[footsteps]

1032
01:01:00.819 --> 01:01:02.520
[compass beeping fast]

1033
01:01:02.687 --> 01:01:06.620
[uplifting music]

1034
01:01:06.786 --> 01:01:09.319
[thunder rumbles]

1035
01:01:11.520 --> 01:01:16.786
[ominous music]

1036
01:01:30.253 --> 01:01:32.586
[thunder rumbles]

1037
01:01:36.520 --> 01:01:38.253
[compass beeping fast]

1038
01:01:38.420 --> 01:01:42.786
[tense music]

1039
01:01:47.620 --> 01:01:52.186
[wave shushing]

1040
01:01:54.186 --> 01:01:56.219
[footsteps approaching]

1041
01:01:56.386 --> 01:01:57.752
[ominous music]

1042
01:01:57.919 --> 01:02:01.620
-He hath made everything
beautiful in this world.

1043
01:02:04.687 --> 01:02:07.886
He hath set eternity
in the hearts of men.

1044
01:02:08.253 --> 01:02:09.852
yet they cannot fathom

1045
01:02:10.219 --> 01:02:13.219
what God has done
from beginning to end.

1046
01:02:13.386 --> 01:02:14.486
[slams book]

1047
01:02:14.653 --> 01:02:17.719
[footsteps approaching]

1048
01:02:22.719 --> 01:02:24.420
Are you afraid of me?

1049
01:02:26.319 --> 01:02:28.786
-I...

1050
01:02:28.953 --> 01:02:32.819
I... I do not fear you. lord.

1051
01:02:33.687 --> 01:02:34.719
-Good.

1052
01:02:36.353 --> 01:02:38.420
You have nothing to fear here.

1053
01:02:41.520 --> 01:02:43.253
I knew your father well.

1054
01:02:44.253 --> 01:02:47.186
He served me loyally
for decades.

1055
01:02:47.353 --> 01:02:49.486
hunting down my greatest enemy.

1056
01:02:52.486 --> 01:02:55.520
-So it was out there
that my father died for you.

1057
01:02:56.486 --> 01:02:58.186
-Oh. no. no. no.

1058
01:02:59.353 --> 01:03:01.386
He sacrificed himself for you...

1059
01:03:02.752 --> 01:03:05.386
to bring you to Argos.
to a better life.

1060
01:03:05.553 --> 01:03:06.886
To me.

1061
01:03:07.253 --> 01:03:10.386
[church bell rings]

1062
01:03:10.553 --> 01:03:13.453
Are you ready
to prove your loyalty?

1063
01:03:14.520 --> 01:03:18.186
Keep a close eye
on that Fig rider.

1064
01:03:23.652 --> 01:03:24.887
[door opens]

1065
01:03:25.253 --> 01:03:28.852
[footsteps]

1066
01:03:29.219 --> 01:03:30.719
-I need to go through
the Storm Horizon.

1067
01:03:32.319 --> 01:03:33.118
-You should be resting. kid.

1068
01:03:33.120 --> 01:03:35.186
-Hammerhead did it.
I can too.

1069
01:03:35.887 --> 01:03:37.520
-He's not who you think he is.

1070
01:03:38.852 --> 01:03:40.353
-I saw him. Larry.

1071
01:03:40.520 --> 01:03:41.686
I saw the Hammerhead go
through the storm.

1072
01:03:41.852 --> 01:03:43.253
-Nobody goes through the storm.

1073
01:03:43.420 --> 01:03:44.786
-He did.

1074
01:03:44.953 --> 01:03:46.386
Who is he. huh?

1075
01:03:49.353 --> 01:03:52.553
-He's a ghost
from a time long past.

1076
01:03:53.453 --> 01:03:55.486
A seed planted
in people's minds.

1077
01:03:56.719 --> 01:03:58.386
Now. I don't know
who you think you saw.

1078
01:03:58.553 --> 01:04:01.686
What I do know is you need
to learn to catch lightning.

1079
01:04:01.853 --> 01:04:02.786
Come on.

1080
01:04:02.953 --> 01:04:05.453
[footsteps departing]

1081
01:04:08.520 --> 01:04:11.887
[thunder rumbles]

1082
01:04:12.253 --> 01:04:13.920
[ominous music]

1083
01:04:18.820 --> 01:04:20.453
-You're holding back too much.

1084
01:04:21.786 --> 01:04:22.820
More speed!

1085
01:04:23.186 --> 01:04:25.719
[engine humming]

1086
01:04:25.887 --> 01:04:27.853
[tense music]

1087
01:04:29.920 --> 01:04:31.585
-You're circling too wide!

1088
01:04:32.652 --> 01:04:34.186
Speed!

1089
01:04:34.353 --> 01:04:35.719
More speed!

1090
01:04:35.887 --> 01:04:37.386
Speed!

1091
01:04:38.420 --> 01:04:39.887
Speed!

1092
01:04:40.253 --> 01:04:45.319
[eerie music]

1093
01:04:45.486 --> 01:04:46.520
More speed!

1094
01:04:46.686 --> 01:04:48.453
[machine whirring]

1095
01:04:50.719 --> 01:04:52.253
[boats explode]

1096
01:04:54.686 --> 01:04:57.219
[machine clicks]

1097
01:04:57.386 --> 01:04:59.219
[eerie music fades]

1098
01:04:59.386 --> 01:05:01.219
[water splashes]

1099
01:05:01.386 --> 01:05:05.253
[panting]

1100
01:05:05.420 --> 01:05:06.887
-Your mind races too much.

1101
01:05:07.253 --> 01:05:09.286
That's just fear
playing tricks on you.

1102
01:05:09.453 --> 01:05:11.186
You have to tame your fear.

1103
01:05:11.353 --> 01:05:13.953
You have to trust it.
to let it take you.

1104
01:05:15.286 --> 01:05:17.353
And the only brake
you have to pull

1105
01:05:17.520 --> 01:05:19.319
is the one
in your imagination.

1106
01:05:20.619 --> 01:05:23.453
We're done for the day.
Now. get your back fixed.

1107
01:05:24.386 --> 01:05:26.319
You look rough. kid.

1108
01:05:28.820 --> 01:05:32.420
[liquid squelching]

1109
01:05:32.585 --> 01:05:33.787
[pestle thumps]

1110
01:05:46.186 --> 01:05:49.953
-[Ana] <i>Is it true that</i>
<i>you can see destinies?</i>

1111
01:05:56.286 --> 01:05:56.853
[gasps]

1112
01:05:57.219 --> 01:05:58.552
Relax.

1113
01:05:58.720 --> 01:06:00.753
You can express
your pain honestly.

1114
01:06:02.219 --> 01:06:04.853
So you ride
for the Founders?

1115
01:06:05.219 --> 01:06:07.853
-I ride for my island.
and to find out the truth.

1116
01:06:08.219 --> 01:06:09.253
-What truth?

1117
01:06:10.420 --> 01:06:11.920
-The truth
that I promised someone.

1118
01:06:12.820 --> 01:06:14.720
-[chuckles]
A woman?

1119
01:06:14.887 --> 01:06:16.152
-Um-hmm.

1120
01:06:16.154 --> 01:06:18.453
-You want to win her place
and bring her here?

1121
01:06:18.619 --> 01:06:20.686
-Well. she's already here.

1122
01:06:20.853 --> 01:06:23.186
She's in a fake tree
in my room.

1123
01:06:25.253 --> 01:06:26.686
-Excuse me.

1124
01:06:27.787 --> 01:06:30.186
I'll take you to a specialist
who might be able to help.

1125
01:06:30.353 --> 01:06:35.186
[ominous music]

1126
01:06:43.853 --> 01:06:47.452
[suspenseful music]

1127
01:06:50.219 --> 01:06:53.219
-What brings you
to the sanctum of Tarus?

1128
01:06:56.953 --> 01:06:58.286
-Neb's a Storm Rider.

1129
01:06:58.452 --> 01:07:00.386
He's badly injured
and needs your help.

1130
01:07:00.552 --> 01:07:02.219
-He doesn't need our help.

1131
01:07:03.219 --> 01:07:06.653
He is the one
I warned Lord Tarus about.

1132
01:07:11.219 --> 01:07:14.585
He is the one
that will breach the storm.

1133
01:07:18.519 --> 01:07:20.585
-Who do you ride for. boy?

1134
01:07:22.920 --> 01:07:24.419
-Baroness.

1135
01:07:24.585 --> 01:07:27.519
-Does she know
that you are here?

1136
01:07:30.585 --> 01:07:32.687
-This was a mistake.
Come on. let's go.

1137
01:07:36.485 --> 01:07:38.585
[tense music]

1138
01:07:38.753 --> 01:07:39.853
-Let them go.

1139
01:07:59.186 --> 01:08:01.787
[indistinct whisper]

1140
01:08:01.953 --> 01:08:03.753
[suspenseful music]

1141
01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:05.720
-[Neb] <i>Bombheads never roam.</i>

1142
01:08:05.887 --> 01:08:07.118
Hey.

1143
01:08:07.120 --> 01:08:09.887
<i>They stay in the temple.</i>
<i>Someone sent him.</i>

1144
01:08:10.253 --> 01:08:11.552
It was you.

1145
01:08:12.787 --> 01:08:14.920
-Could have just as easily
been you in her place.

1146
01:08:15.286 --> 01:08:16.186
-Why?!

1147
01:08:17.519 --> 01:08:18.820
-Do you want vengeance?

1148
01:08:20.352 --> 01:08:22.319
Do it out there on the water.

1149
01:08:22.485 --> 01:08:24.920
Not here.
Not like this.

1150
01:08:25.286 --> 01:08:26.853
She brought her death
upon herself.

1151
01:08:27.219 --> 01:08:28.720
[tense music]

1152
01:08:28.887 --> 01:08:30.219
-Hey!

1153
01:08:36.853 --> 01:08:39.552
[footsteps running]

1154
01:08:40.887 --> 01:08:42.286
[groans]

1155
01:08:45.186 --> 01:08:48.352
[tense music continues]

1156
01:08:57.586 --> 01:08:58.620
[grunts]

1157
01:08:59.687 --> 01:09:03.452
[water splashes]

1158
01:09:11.352 --> 01:09:12.920
[panting]

1159
01:09:13.286 --> 01:09:14.720
[grunts]

1160
01:09:16.553 --> 01:09:17.953
What did you tell her?!

1161
01:09:18.318 --> 01:09:19.520
[water splashes]

1162
01:09:19.687 --> 01:09:25.318
[tense music]

1163
01:09:32.485 --> 01:09:36.285
-Lord Tarus.
I made a vow to Lord Tarus

1164
01:09:36.452 --> 01:09:38.385
to always protect the storm.

1165
01:09:38.553 --> 01:09:39.953
Always protect the storm.

1166
01:09:40.318 --> 01:09:42.820
-I'll see you out on the water.

1167
01:09:43.186 --> 01:09:44.485
[water splashes]

1168
01:09:44.653 --> 01:09:46.620
[tense music fades]

1169
01:09:46.787 --> 01:09:49.253
[ominous music]

1170
01:09:49.419 --> 01:09:53.920
[machine beeping]

1171
01:10:03.787 --> 01:10:05.486
-What did you find out?

1172
01:10:13.553 --> 01:10:14.787
Tell me about him.

1173
01:10:16.687 --> 01:10:18.352
-He's just...

1174
01:10:19.887 --> 01:10:21.553
...a Gaya-worshiping heathen.

1175
01:10:21.720 --> 01:10:22.853
-Insolent girl.

1176
01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:24.887
You know that word
is forbidden here.

1177
01:10:27.318 --> 01:10:28.953
-She speaks the truth

1178
01:10:29.318 --> 01:10:31.318
even if we don't want
to hear it.

1179
01:10:33.553 --> 01:10:37.285
Tell me what the Storm Rider
said about Gaya.

1180
01:10:37.453 --> 01:10:39.218
-He spoke of an ancient ritual.

1181
01:10:39.385 --> 01:10:40.853
He's badly injured.

1182
01:10:41.953 --> 01:10:44.154
-Ancient ritual.

1183
01:10:45.186 --> 01:10:46.953
What sort of ancient ritual?

1184
01:10:49.720 --> 01:10:55.252
-Well. these pagans plant trees
when someone is born

1185
01:10:55.420 --> 01:10:56.920
or when someone dies.

1186
01:10:58.385 --> 01:11:00.753
He's no threat
to you. Lord Tarus.

1187
01:11:00.920 --> 01:11:02.520
He believes his lost love
lives in a tree.

1188
01:11:02.687 --> 01:11:04.586
and that a Titan hides
on the island.

1189
01:11:06.285 --> 01:11:07.653
-A Titan?

1190
01:11:08.953 --> 01:11:11.753
-He makes no sense
when he speaks.

1191
01:11:11.920 --> 01:11:14.285
-What Titan?

1192
01:11:22.653 --> 01:11:23.853
Tell me.

1193
01:11:27.653 --> 01:11:29.318
-Sykeus.

1194
01:11:30.420 --> 01:11:31.753
-[sighs]

1195
01:11:33.853 --> 01:11:37.853
Your father would be so.
so proud.

1196
01:11:40.920 --> 01:11:42.185
-[sighs in relief]

1197
01:11:43.453 --> 01:11:45.787
[panting]

1198
01:11:45.953 --> 01:11:47.720
[ominous music fades]

1199
01:11:47.887 --> 01:11:49.820
[wind blowing]

1200
01:11:50.153 --> 01:11:52.285
[ominous music]

1201
01:12:06.953 --> 01:12:08.218
-[Ana] <i>Is it true?</i>

1202
01:12:08.386 --> 01:12:09.720
[voice echoing]

1203
01:12:12.787 --> 01:12:14.453
<i>That you can see destinies?</i>

1204
01:12:14.620 --> 01:12:15.586
[voice echoing]

1205
01:12:24.218 --> 01:12:26.553
-[Neb] <i>If what the Baroness</i>
<i>told me is true.</i>

1206
01:12:26.720 --> 01:12:28.520
<i>then I must make good</i>
<i>on my promise.</i>

1207
01:12:29.520 --> 01:12:30.953
<i>Amor fati.</i>

1208
01:12:31.318 --> 01:12:35.185
[suspenseful music]

1209
01:12:36.553 --> 01:12:37.653
-Larry.

1210
01:12:38.687 --> 01:12:39.953
[suspenseful music]

1211
01:12:40.319 --> 01:12:43.953
I've got a plan.
and I need your help.

1212
01:12:47.218 --> 01:12:50.319
[distant audience cheering]

1213
01:12:50.486 --> 01:12:51.486
-[Race Announcer]
<i>Broadcasting live</i>

1214
01:12:51.653 --> 01:12:52.785
<i>from the walls of Argos.</i>

1215
01:12:52.787 --> 01:12:56.553
<i>this is the second</i>
<i>and final race of the cycle.</i>

1216
01:12:56.720 --> 01:12:58.252
<i>The first one</i>
<i>went tragically bad</i>

1217
01:12:58.420 --> 01:12:59.785
<i>for one of the Baroness' riders.</i>

1218
01:12:59.787 --> 01:13:02.553
<i>making Fig Island [indistinct]</i>
<i>last hope for Argos residents</i>

1219
01:13:02.720 --> 01:13:04.420
<i>on their remaining Storm Rider.</i>

1220
01:13:04.586 --> 01:13:05.818
<i>Choppy seas</i>
<i>as the surface wind blows</i>

1221
01:13:05.820 --> 01:13:08.953
<i>around Neptune's Rock</i>
<i>currently at 15 miles per hour</i>

1222
01:13:09.319 --> 01:13:11.319
<i>as the Storm Riders align</i>
<i>in close proximity.</i>

1223
01:13:11.486 --> 01:13:12.820
<i>awaiting for the countdown.</i>

1224
01:13:14.853 --> 01:13:16.653
<i>This is a drag race</i>
<i>from starting point</i>

1225
01:13:16.820 --> 01:13:18.853
<i>to Neptune's Rock</i>
<i>and back again.</i>

1226
01:13:19.218 --> 01:13:20.820
<i>Winners win a place on Argos.</i>

1227
01:13:21.185 --> 01:13:23.453
<i>Losers are cast out</i>
<i>to the open sea.</i>

1228
01:13:23.620 --> 01:13:28.653
[tense music]

1229
01:13:28.820 --> 01:13:32.920
<i>Five. four. three. two. one.</i>

1230
01:13:33.286 --> 01:13:33.885
<i>And they're off.</i>

1231
01:13:33.887 --> 01:13:35.218
[machine accelerating]

1232
01:13:36.653 --> 01:13:38.620
[water splashing]

1233
01:13:44.787 --> 01:13:45.887
[machine whirring]

1234
01:13:46.253 --> 01:13:48.520
[engine humming]

1235
01:13:50.653 --> 01:13:52.620
<i>Bombhead bumps</i>
<i>into Fig Island's rider</i>

1236
01:13:52.787 --> 01:13:55.520
<i>almost taunting him.</i>
<i>sending a clear message</i>

1237
01:13:55.687 --> 01:13:57.620
<i>and one</i>
<i>that seems to be personal.</i>

1238
01:13:59.887 --> 01:14:02.253
[engine humming]

1239
01:14:02.420 --> 01:14:03.720
[metal clinks]

1240
01:14:06.353 --> 01:14:08.253
<i>The Storm Riders</i>
<i>are approaching Neptune's Rock.</i>

1241
01:14:09.953 --> 01:14:11.286
<i>Fig Island rider.</i>
<i>in second place.</i>

1242
01:14:11.453 --> 01:14:12.284
<i>cuts in on the inside.</i>

1243
01:14:12.286 --> 01:14:13.785
<i>hugging the rail</i>
<i>right behind him</i>

1244
01:14:13.787 --> 01:14:16.420
<i>as the rider from [indistinct]</i>
<i>Rose fighting for position</i>

1245
01:14:16.586 --> 01:14:18.286
<i>while Argos' rider</i>
<i>remains in the lead</i>

1246
01:14:18.453 --> 01:14:20.653
<i>as he powers through</i>
<i>toward the finish line.</i>

1247
01:14:21.520 --> 01:14:24.420
[audience cheering
and applauding]

1248
01:14:24.586 --> 01:14:25.785
<i>We all know the rules. folks.</i>

1249
01:14:25.787 --> 01:14:29.853
<i>If Argos' rider wins.</i>
<i>then all other islands lose.</i>

1250
01:14:31.887 --> 01:14:33.920
[engine humming]

1251
01:14:37.153 --> 01:14:38.286
[engine accelerating]

1252
01:14:38.453 --> 01:14:40.420
[water splashing]

1253
01:14:43.253 --> 01:14:46.620
[suspenseful music]

1254
01:14:52.720 --> 01:14:53.920
[thunder rumbles]

1255
01:15:02.920 --> 01:15:03.753
[engine accelerating]

1256
01:15:06.353 --> 01:15:07.820
[lightning static]

1257
01:15:09.787 --> 01:15:12.353
<i>And the Fig Island's rider</i>
<i>catches the lightning bolt.</i>

1258
01:15:12.520 --> 01:15:13.685
<i>giving him the boost.</i>

1259
01:15:13.687 --> 01:15:16.353
<i>He passes the Argos rider</i>
<i>and gets in the lead.</i>

1260
01:15:16.520 --> 01:15:17.553
<i>What a move!</i>

1261
01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:19.253
[lightning buzzing]

1262
01:15:24.753 --> 01:15:27.553
<i>The Fig Island's rider advances</i>
<i>toward the finish line.</i>

1263
01:15:27.720 --> 01:15:29.753
<i>He rides</i>
<i>with the power of thunder.</i>

1264
01:15:29.919 --> 01:15:33.553
[lightning buzzing]

1265
01:15:33.720 --> 01:15:36.453
<i>And he wins. the Fig win.</i>

1266
01:15:36.620 --> 01:15:39.386
<i>Oh my goodness.</i>
<i>Who would have thought?</i>

1267
01:15:39.553 --> 01:15:43.186
[audience cheering]

1268
01:15:43.353 --> 01:15:44.952
<i>Argos' rider comes in second.</i>

1269
01:15:45.319 --> 01:15:47.787
<i>What an amazing finish</i>
<i>for the rider of Fig</i>

1270
01:15:47.952 --> 01:15:50.952
as his home island
rejoices in redemption.

1271
01:15:51.319 --> 01:15:53.853
[engine humming]

1272
01:15:54.219 --> 01:15:56.720
<i>But the Fig rider</i>
<i>doesn't seem to be stopping.</i>

1273
01:15:56.887 --> 01:15:58.553
<i>He appears to be turning around.</i>

1274
01:15:59.853 --> 01:16:01.586
[machine whirring]

1275
01:16:01.753 --> 01:16:04.186
<i>What is the Storm Rider up to?</i>

1276
01:16:04.353 --> 01:16:05.687
[engine accelerates. whirring]

1277
01:16:05.853 --> 01:16:10.420
[engine humming]

1278
01:16:10.586 --> 01:16:11.553
<i>He's getting</i>
<i>on the collision course</i>

1279
01:16:11.720 --> 01:16:12.785
<i>with the Argos rider.</i>

1280
01:16:12.787 --> 01:16:15.486
<i>Folks. I've never seen</i>
<i>anything like this.</i>

1281
01:16:15.653 --> 01:16:18.253
<i>This will not sit well</i>
<i>with our lord Founders.</i>

1282
01:16:18.420 --> 01:16:20.186
[engines humming]

1283
01:16:20.353 --> 01:16:21.787
<i>This blood feud</i>
<i>is about to get settled.</i>

1284
01:16:21.952 --> 01:16:27.286
[engines accelerating]

1285
01:16:27.453 --> 01:16:28.653
[water splashes]

1286
01:16:28.820 --> 01:16:30.118
[boats explode]

1287
01:16:30.120 --> 01:16:32.853
<i>An awful explosion signals</i>
<i>the end of Fig Island's rider</i>

1288
01:16:33.219 --> 01:16:36.186
<i>and his pagan island's hope</i>
<i>for Argos residence.</i>

1289
01:16:37.720 --> 01:16:38.653
[oxygen tank hisses underwater]

1290
01:16:38.820 --> 01:16:40.886
[indistinct distant shouting]

1291
01:16:41.253 --> 01:16:42.919
<i>In all my years reporting</i>
<i>for the wall.</i>

1292
01:16:43.286 --> 01:16:45.420
<i>I've never seen</i>
<i>such reckless behavior</i>

1293
01:16:45.586 --> 01:16:47.720
<i>displayed by a Storm Rider.</i>

1294
01:16:47.886 --> 01:16:50.753
[indistinct distant shouting]

1295
01:17:02.253 --> 01:17:03.852
<i>The gates of Argos</i>
<i>will remain closed</i>

1296
01:17:04.219 --> 01:17:06.852
<i>to the Island of Fig.</i>
<i>as they should.</i>

1297
01:17:07.219 --> 01:17:10.520
-Baroness. when were you last
on Fig Island?

1298
01:17:11.420 --> 01:17:13.253
-About six months ago.

1299
01:17:13.420 --> 01:17:15.886
-And who did you see?

1300
01:17:16.253 --> 01:17:19.520
-The Storm Riders
I selected for the last cycle.

1301
01:17:19.687 --> 01:17:23.586
[distant audience chanting]

1302
01:17:23.753 --> 01:17:25.453
-Who else?

1303
01:17:25.620 --> 01:17:28.520
[tense music]

1304
01:17:36.886 --> 01:17:41.286
To think I've been looking
for Sykeus this whole time.

1305
01:17:41.453 --> 01:17:45.253
when my general.
the face of Argos.

1306
01:17:45.420 --> 01:17:48.886
knew exactly
where he was all this time.

1307
01:17:50.420 --> 01:17:52.720
My searchers will arrive
on Fig Island.

1308
01:17:52.886 --> 01:17:55.720
and they will find the source
and see how deep it runs.

1309
01:17:55.886 --> 01:17:58.219
and then they will find Sykeus

1310
01:17:58.386 --> 01:18:00.786
and bring him back to the city
he helped build.

1311
01:18:00.952 --> 01:18:03.786
and hang him in the square.

1312
01:18:03.952 --> 01:18:06.586
-You'll have to kill me first.

1313
01:18:06.753 --> 01:18:10.486
-Do you remember
taking the element?

1314
01:18:10.653 --> 01:18:14.420
What it felt like
to taste immortality?

1315
01:18:14.586 --> 01:18:18.186
Because now. you will go back
to where it all began

1316
01:18:18.353 --> 01:18:20.819
and be faced with a choice.

1317
01:18:21.186 --> 01:18:24.620
Starve to death or once again.
take the element

1318
01:18:24.786 --> 01:18:27.420
and choke on your own hypocrisy!

1319
01:18:30.253 --> 01:18:31.886
Take her to the well!

1320
01:18:32.253 --> 01:18:35.520
[tense music continues]

1321
01:18:45.720 --> 01:18:46.786
-[Radio Announcer]
<i>After 50 years.</i>

1322
01:18:46.953 --> 01:18:48.653
<i>the wanted criminal Sykeus.</i>

1323
01:18:48.819 --> 01:18:50.819
<i>known by the pagans</i>
<i>as Hammerhead</i>

1324
01:18:51.186 --> 01:18:53.319
<i>has been located on Fig Island.</i>

1325
01:18:53.486 --> 01:18:55.819
<i>All Argos' forces</i>
<i>have been deployed.</i>

1326
01:18:57.520 --> 01:19:00.919
[tense music continues]

1327
01:19:09.886 --> 01:19:13.286
[fire crackling]

1328
01:19:13.453 --> 01:19:15.886
[water splashing]

1329
01:19:17.453 --> 01:19:21.286
[suspenseful music]

1330
01:19:21.453 --> 01:19:23.286
-[Larry] <i>At this</i>
point in the race.

1331
01:19:23.453 --> 01:19:24.852
<i>you'll be by the walls.</i>

1332
01:19:25.219 --> 01:19:26.852
<i>You'll have to swim</i>
<i>to the shore from there.</i>

1333
01:19:27.686 --> 01:19:29.653
[chain clinking]

1334
01:19:32.553 --> 01:19:36.186
[suspenseful music continues]

1335
01:19:49.819 --> 01:19:51.686
<i>You can enter</i>
<i>the Temple of Founders</i>

1336
01:19:51.852 --> 01:19:54.553
<i>through the passage</i>
<i>under the water.</i>

1337
01:19:57.586 --> 01:20:00.786
<i>But once you reach this point.</i>
<i>the rest is up to you.</i>

1338
01:20:03.852 --> 01:20:07.386
[compass beeping]

1339
01:20:14.686 --> 01:20:16.386
[compass beeping fast]

1340
01:20:16.553 --> 01:20:20.553
[compass beeping slows down]

1341
01:20:30.719 --> 01:20:34.219
<i>You will not be alone.</i>
<i>the sharks will swim with you.</i>

1342
01:20:35.286 --> 01:20:36.520
[water splashes softly]

1343
01:20:53.887 --> 01:20:58.186
[ominous music]

1344
01:20:58.353 --> 01:20:59.719
[sword unsheathes]

1345
01:21:01.853 --> 01:21:07.319
[ominous music fades]

1346
01:21:10.386 --> 01:21:13.652
[suspenseful music]

1347
01:21:17.853 --> 01:21:21.752
[ominous music]

1348
01:21:25.920 --> 01:21:30.619
[suspenseful music]

1349
01:21:38.686 --> 01:21:44.420
[slow footsteps]

1350
01:21:48.585 --> 01:21:49.920
[body thumps softly]

1351
01:21:50.286 --> 01:21:51.353
[guns click]

1352
01:21:53.353 --> 01:21:54.520
-Neb.

1353
01:21:56.752 --> 01:21:59.486
I've waited a long time
for this moment.

1354
01:22:00.585 --> 01:22:04.552
The question you fear to ask
holds the answer that you seek.

1355
01:22:05.386 --> 01:22:07.820
So go ahead. ask.

1356
01:22:08.686 --> 01:22:10.552
-Who's the Hammerhead?

1357
01:22:10.719 --> 01:22:12.953
-In the past or the future?

1358
01:22:14.920 --> 01:22:16.787
Your grandfather
never told you?

1359
01:22:18.519 --> 01:22:21.787
I'm sure he did
in his own way.

1360
01:22:22.920 --> 01:22:24.652
Myths and legends.

1361
01:22:25.953 --> 01:22:27.953
He told you about Gaya. right?

1362
01:22:29.519 --> 01:22:31.219
And the last Titan?

1363
01:22:31.386 --> 01:22:35.453
[sentimental music]

1364
01:22:43.219 --> 01:22:46.619
I have seen a rider
enter the storm.

1365
01:22:46.787 --> 01:22:47.517
[voice echoes]

1366
01:22:47.519 --> 01:22:50.686
He was of your blood. Sykeus.

1367
01:23:10.286 --> 01:23:11.953
-Bring me the Baroness.

1368
01:23:20.452 --> 01:23:25.420
-You see. Neb. I too
was told stories growing up.

1369
01:23:28.485 --> 01:23:31.552
And I too have seen the truth.

1370
01:23:42.920 --> 01:23:46.452
And I have seen
a rider enter the storm.

1371
01:23:47.787 --> 01:23:50.753
[thunder rumbling]

1372
01:23:55.720 --> 01:23:58.353
But the thing with visions.

1373
01:23:58.519 --> 01:24:04.619
sometimes you see them
and sometimes you live them.

1374
01:24:08.853 --> 01:24:10.619
Was there a question?

1375
01:24:10.787 --> 01:24:14.619
[suspenseful music]

1376
01:24:17.687 --> 01:24:19.253
-[Young Ana] <i>Is it true?</i>

1377
01:24:19.419 --> 01:24:21.319
<i>-[Young Neb]Is what true?</i>

1378
01:24:21.485 --> 01:24:22.887
-[Young Ana] <i>That you</i>
can see destinies.

1379
01:24:24.419 --> 01:24:28.286
[indistinct whispers]

1380
01:24:28.452 --> 01:24:29.485
-[Ana] <i>What can you really see?</i>

1381
01:24:30.787 --> 01:24:33.820
-[Neb] <i>Images. Fragments.</i>

1382
01:24:34.186 --> 01:24:35.452
<i>Like pieces in a puzzle.</i>

1383
01:24:36.519 --> 01:24:37.820
<i>I saw the Hammerhead</i>
<i>go through the storm.</i>

1384
01:24:38.154 --> 01:24:40.286
-[Dida] <i>Nobody goes</i>
through the storm.

1385
01:24:40.452 --> 01:24:41.653
[indistinct whispers]

1386
01:24:41.820 --> 01:24:42.953
-[Neb] <i>Who is he. huh?</i>

1387
01:24:44.385 --> 01:24:47.319
-What have you seen. Neb?

1388
01:24:47.485 --> 01:24:50.820
-[Nikola] <i>He's a ghost</i>
<i>with a long past.</i>

1389
01:24:51.186 --> 01:24:53.419
<i>-</i> [Baronness]
<i>Sometimes you see them</i>

1390
01:24:53.586 --> 01:24:55.687
<i>and sometimes</i>
<i>you live them.</i>

1391
01:24:55.853 --> 01:24:57.820
[indistinct whispers]

1392
01:24:58.186 --> 01:24:59.920
-[Dida] <i>What did you see?</i>
[voice echoes]

1393
01:25:00.286 --> 01:25:01.419
-[Neb] <i>Who is he?</i>
[voice echoes]

1394
01:25:01.586 --> 01:25:03.253
-[Maia] <i>Is it true?</i>

1395
01:25:03.419 --> 01:25:04.552
<i>That you can see destinies?</i>

1396
01:25:04.720 --> 01:25:06.419
-[Neb] <i>Who is the Hammerhead.</i>

1397
01:25:06.586 --> 01:25:09.787
<i>-</i> [Baronness] In the
past or the future?

1398
01:25:09.953 --> 01:25:11.452
[sentimental music]

1399
01:25:11.620 --> 01:25:13.720
-They call him Hammerhead.

1400
01:25:13.887 --> 01:25:17.620
Legend has it.
he self-sacrificed to the storm.

1401
01:25:17.787 --> 01:25:21.419
And ever since.
he became the Knight of Gaya.

1402
01:25:21.586 --> 01:25:23.186
the Son of Storm.

1403
01:25:23.352 --> 01:25:27.586
[uplifting music]

1404
01:25:27.753 --> 01:25:29.586
-Why do they call him
Hammerhead?

1405
01:25:29.753 --> 01:25:32.419
-Some believe
that hammerhead shark

1406
01:25:32.586 --> 01:25:36.519
can see things happen
before they actually do.

1407
01:25:36.687 --> 01:25:37.653
[engine accelerates]

1408
01:25:37.820 --> 01:25:39.253
[engine whirring]

1409
01:25:41.186 --> 01:25:43.452
-He was named after a shark.

1410
01:25:43.620 --> 01:25:48.253
He has a thousand eyes
that can see everywhere--

1411
01:25:48.419 --> 01:25:52.253
from the side
and even in the back.

1412
01:25:56.419 --> 01:25:58.553
[uplifting music continues]

1413
01:25:58.720 --> 01:26:02.452
-It is believed that Hammerhead
hides in the storm

1414
01:26:02.620 --> 01:26:05.920
and ventures
where no others dare to go.

1415
01:26:06.285 --> 01:26:08.853
[engine humming]

1416
01:26:09.219 --> 01:26:10.953
And one day.

1417
01:26:11.318 --> 01:26:14.485
he will lead all of us
to our new home.

1418
01:26:19.887 --> 01:26:21.787
[water splashing]

1419
01:26:23.887 --> 01:26:27.419
[uplifting music]

1420
01:26:36.720 --> 01:26:41.787
[water splashing]

1421
01:26:48.186 --> 01:26:48.787
[uplifting music fades]

1422
01:26:48.953 --> 01:26:50.787
[footsteps]

1423
01:26:50.953 --> 01:26:53.186
[distant thunder rumbling]

1424
01:27:00.953 --> 01:27:03.753
-How far must you go. Tarus?

1425
01:27:03.920 --> 01:27:06.252
-To the end of the world
and back.

1426
01:27:06.419 --> 01:27:07.453
Just as we planned.

1427
01:27:07.620 --> 01:27:08.620
-[sighs]

1428
01:27:10.787 --> 01:27:12.318
No.

1429
01:27:12.486 --> 01:27:15.385
No. the plan
was to save our world.

1430
01:27:15.553 --> 01:27:17.285
not to destroy another.

1431
01:27:17.453 --> 01:27:21.687
-I created this world
because Gaya destroyed ours.

1432
01:27:22.687 --> 01:27:24.887
-They were your friends.

1433
01:27:25.252 --> 01:27:26.586
-We had a history. yes.

1434
01:27:27.853 --> 01:27:29.520
But not a future.

1435
01:27:30.953 --> 01:27:33.920
The question is. do you?

1436
01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:38.553
When you die.
the past dies with you.

1437
01:27:39.753 --> 01:27:41.185
where it began.

1438
01:27:42.318 --> 01:27:46.285
The people we were.
all of it just ends.

1439
01:27:47.687 --> 01:27:49.385
Like the man I used to be

1440
01:27:50.586 --> 01:27:52.853
usurped by the god
that I am becoming.

1441
01:27:53.720 --> 01:27:55.420
-So what's stopping you?

1442
01:27:55.586 --> 01:27:58.820
[suspenseful music]

1443
01:28:06.420 --> 01:28:08.687
-[Neb] <i>Time is a</i>
twisted illusion.

1444
01:28:08.853 --> 01:28:12.853
<i>a force that dares us</i>
<i>to chase it. to outrun it.</i>

1445
01:28:13.218 --> 01:28:16.586
<i>The past may cast its shadow</i>
<i>reaching for the future.</i>

1446
01:28:16.753 --> 01:28:19.352
<i>but nothing can hold destiny</i>
<i>when its time has come.</i>

1447
01:28:21.820 --> 01:28:23.520
-What is that?

1448
01:28:23.687 --> 01:28:24.620
What is that?!

1449
01:28:24.787 --> 01:28:26.586
[compass beeping]

1450
01:28:26.753 --> 01:28:29.586
You. you are behind this.

1451
01:28:29.753 --> 01:28:33.420
-I am where I am fated to be.

1452
01:28:33.586 --> 01:28:35.720
[engine accelerates]

1453
01:28:41.687 --> 01:28:42.920
[water splashing]

1454
01:28:43.285 --> 01:28:44.787
[cheering]

1455
01:28:44.953 --> 01:28:50.787
[uplifting music]

1456
01:28:50.953 --> 01:28:53.353
-Hammerhead. Hammerhead.
He's back! He's back!

1457
01:28:55.453 --> 01:28:57.486
-He'll never make it.
He'll never make it.

1458
01:28:57.653 --> 01:28:59.353
Hunt him down!

1459
01:28:59.520 --> 01:29:01.720
[water splashing]

1460
01:29:09.553 --> 01:29:12.252
[tense music]

1461
01:29:16.486 --> 01:29:19.353
[water splashing]

1462
01:29:20.620 --> 01:29:25.687
[cheering]

1463
01:29:25.853 --> 01:29:28.486
-[Neb] <i>That war</i>
<i>Dida talked about.</i>

1464
01:29:28.653 --> 01:29:30.185
<i>was never his war.</i>

1465
01:29:30.353 --> 01:29:32.353
<i>This is our war.</i>

1466
01:29:32.520 --> 01:29:35.353
[water splashing]

1467
01:29:37.285 --> 01:29:40.953
[tense music continues]

1468
01:29:59.720 --> 01:30:02.820
[engine whirring]

1469
01:30:03.185 --> 01:30:06.319
[engine humming]

1470
01:30:15.319 --> 01:30:17.185
[machine clicks]
[engine whirring]

1471
01:30:21.553 --> 01:30:24.687
[engine humming]

1472
01:30:24.853 --> 01:30:26.286
[suspenseful music fades]

1473
01:30:27.653 --> 01:30:31.319
[suspenseful music]

1474
01:30:34.185 --> 01:30:37.420
[ominous music]

1475
01:30:37.586 --> 01:30:38.520
[thunder rumbles]

1476
01:30:38.687 --> 01:30:39.720
[lightning static]

1477
01:30:39.887 --> 01:30:42.553
[boats exploding]

1478
